1
00:00:42,457 --> 00:00:44,760
(After the men's mothers' picks,
Kang Shin Woo and his mother's room)

2
00:00:46,846 --> 00:00:49,682
Da Hye works until 3 p.m. on Saturdays.

3
00:00:49,682 --> 00:00:51,417
And she has Sundays completely off.

4
00:00:51,650 --> 00:00:52,551
That's perfect.

5
00:00:53,619 --> 00:00:54,587
It's perfect, right?

6
00:00:55,521 --> 00:00:56,555
Yes.

7
00:00:56,555 --> 00:00:59,225
She shot 15 body profiles in a year,

8
00:00:59,225 --> 00:01:00,993
and won two Grand Prix titles.

9
00:01:00,993 --> 00:01:05,464
She runs a Pilates studio in Gangnam.

10
00:01:05,464 --> 00:01:06,665
In Gangnam.

11
00:01:07,266 --> 00:01:08,834
In Gangnam, Mom.

12
00:01:09,668 --> 00:01:12,104
He's trying to win his mom over.

13
00:01:12,104 --> 00:01:13,973
Right. She's so good with adults.

14
00:01:14,273 --> 00:01:17,977
Last night,
when the moms played games together,

15
00:01:17,977 --> 00:01:21,080
Jeong Yoon's mom was sitting next to me.

16
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:23,449
She even makes her own
soybean paste and chili paste.

17
00:01:23,449 --> 00:01:24,850
That's what she was saying.

18
00:01:24,850 --> 00:01:27,686
She even makes kimchi
from 30 cabbages by herself.

19
00:01:27,686 --> 00:01:29,088
Was that charming to you?

20
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:32,124
You can't see it, but they're each
talking up someone else's charms.

21
00:01:32,124 --> 00:01:34,093
They're bringing up different people.

22
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,796
- What the daughter is like matters.
- The daughter is so pretty too.

23
00:01:36,796 --> 00:01:38,597
You can tell a lot
about the daughter by the mother.

24
00:01:38,597 --> 00:01:39,632
No, they can be different.

25
00:01:39,632 --> 00:01:42,702
That's not it. Like mother, like daughter.

26
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:46,472
The more you talk with her,
the more different she may seem.

27
00:01:46,472 --> 00:01:48,340
Are you troubled?

28
00:01:48,340 --> 00:01:49,341
I'm burning up inside.

29
00:01:50,576 --> 00:01:53,112
I never imagined you'd choose...

30
00:01:54,313 --> 00:01:55,247
someone else.

31
00:01:56,048 --> 00:01:59,351
You never know after a one-on-one date.

32
00:02:00,486 --> 00:02:03,989
When I took Shin Woo's hand
and went to Jeong Yoon...

33
00:02:03,989 --> 00:02:06,959
Jeong Yoon is pretty
from every angle, right?

34
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:11,797
So if he gets a closer look,

35
00:02:11,797 --> 00:02:13,632
maybe he'll feel more drawn to her.

36
00:02:13,632 --> 00:02:16,035
I had that bit of confidence too.

37
00:02:16,569 --> 00:02:19,905
First of all, I was a bit troubled.

38
00:02:19,905 --> 00:02:23,342
Because she said she'd show up
in a blue dress yesterday,

39
00:02:23,342 --> 00:02:26,078
and she looked beautiful
in the blue dress.

40
00:02:26,078 --> 00:02:27,213
He's totally fallen for her.
What do we do?

41
00:02:27,213 --> 00:02:28,581
My jaw dropped wide open.

42
00:02:28,581 --> 00:02:30,649
My jaw nearly dropped out of place.

43
00:02:31,384 --> 00:02:34,587
Honestly, I was very single-minded,

44
00:02:34,587 --> 00:02:37,289
so I wanted my mother to choose Da Hye.

45
00:02:38,024 --> 00:02:41,360
I wondered if it was okay
to go eat like that,

46
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,595
whether that was right.

47
00:02:43,462 --> 00:02:46,499
His mother seems to have someone in mind.

48
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:50,436
Since Shin Woo already has Da Hye
in his heart...

49
00:02:50,436 --> 00:02:52,304
It was Da Hye from the start.

50
00:02:52,304 --> 00:02:54,974
So I don't think he'll act that way
with Jeong Yoon.

51
00:02:55,474 --> 00:02:56,609
But this is really amazing.

52
00:02:56,609 --> 00:02:59,011
Honestly, when I was standing there,

53
00:02:59,011 --> 00:03:01,547
I was thinking, "I hope Seong Mo comes."

54
00:03:01,547 --> 00:03:02,982
- Isn't that amazing?
- My goodness.

55
00:03:03,682 --> 00:03:06,886
Yesterday, I was sure about Shin Woo.

56
00:03:06,886 --> 00:03:09,388
Then when asked if I'd choose Seong Mo
to the end, I said no.

57
00:03:09,388 --> 00:03:10,723
You need to experience everyone first.

58
00:03:10,723 --> 00:03:12,625
I said that could change.

59
00:03:12,625 --> 00:03:14,493
For both sides.

60
00:03:14,493 --> 00:03:16,762
For both me and Shin Woo.

61
00:03:16,762 --> 00:03:17,697
Of course.

62
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:19,632
I thought Da Hye would be popular
with the mothers.

63
00:03:19,632 --> 00:03:20,700
Right.

64
00:03:21,267 --> 00:03:23,035
They really do like licensed professions.

65
00:03:23,636 --> 00:03:25,237
- Korean medicine doctor.
- Exactly.

66
00:03:25,237 --> 00:03:27,173
She's popular with the mothers.

67
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:29,075
It's a licensed profession.

68
00:03:29,408 --> 00:03:32,111
I guess that really matters to mothers.

69
00:03:32,111 --> 00:03:34,480
Those job-related factors.

70
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:37,750
Education and jobs can't be ignored.

71
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:40,086
- Mothers still care about that.
- Right.

72
00:03:41,087 --> 00:03:43,489
I thought Do Yoon would be popular too,
but no one picked her.

73
00:03:44,323 --> 00:03:45,257
She's young.

74
00:03:45,257 --> 00:03:46,258
I see.

75
00:03:46,625 --> 00:03:48,794
Mothers don't like it
when someone is too young either.

76
00:03:50,763 --> 00:03:52,898
(0-vote Ahn Do Yoon and her mother
in their room)

77
00:03:52,898 --> 00:03:55,801
All the women are over 30.

78
00:03:55,801 --> 00:03:57,069
People get married late these days,
that's why.

79
00:03:58,637 --> 00:04:01,207
You have plenty of time, right?

80
00:04:01,774 --> 00:04:06,312
Your twenties are for trying things,
so it's fine.

81
00:04:06,612 --> 00:04:08,214
It's good to experience this too.

82
00:04:08,214 --> 00:04:09,148
Right.

83
00:04:09,615 --> 00:04:11,417
It's nothing, Do Yoon.

84
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:13,352
I'm really okay.

85
00:04:13,352 --> 00:04:16,922
It's okay.
It's okay to experience things like this.

86
00:04:18,991 --> 00:04:21,794
Honestly, with the mothers' picks,

87
00:04:21,794 --> 00:04:26,065
I don't know if the mothers
were backing their sons' picks,

88
00:04:26,065 --> 00:04:28,868
or if the sons really left it
entirely to their mothers.

89
00:04:29,101 --> 00:04:30,836
But when I wasn't chosen,

90
00:04:33,873 --> 00:04:36,709
it didn't feel especially good.

91
00:04:37,877 --> 00:04:39,678
I thought the mothers would like me,
but they must not.

92
00:04:41,514 --> 00:04:42,648
Maybe that was just my thought.

93
00:04:48,921 --> 00:04:50,623
Mom, why aren't you answering me?

94
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:52,158
Why aren't you answering me?

95
00:04:54,093 --> 00:04:56,128
What answer would you like to hear?

96
00:04:56,128 --> 00:04:59,398
When I say, "I thought the mothers
would like me, but I guess they don't,"

97
00:04:59,398 --> 00:05:00,966
why won't you answer?

98
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:05,071
Well, how would I know?

99
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:07,073
Her mother must be upset.

100
00:05:07,073 --> 00:05:08,674
It seems like she has something to say,

101
00:05:08,674 --> 00:05:09,875
but she isn't saying it.

102
00:05:10,409 --> 00:05:12,445
The other mothers...

103
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:15,748
comfort their daughters
when they're not chosen.

104
00:05:16,515 --> 00:05:17,349
What comfort?

105
00:05:17,349 --> 00:05:20,219
Maybe you're not comforting me
because I'm not upset.

106
00:05:23,723 --> 00:05:26,625
I knew no one would come.

107
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:28,094
Really?

108
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:30,863
See? I was right, wasn't I?

109
00:05:30,863 --> 00:05:32,231
Ma'am.

110
00:05:32,998 --> 00:05:35,401
Kang Hyeon's impression...

111
00:05:35,401 --> 00:05:39,405
isn't the kind of impression mothers love.

112
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:42,641
I feel like Mom knew
I would not get votes.

113
00:05:42,641 --> 00:05:44,477
But what can I do? This is who I am.

114
00:05:44,477 --> 00:05:47,346
Shouldn't I meet someone
who loves me as I am?

115
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:49,915
Yeah.

116
00:05:49,915 --> 00:05:52,051
Yang Ha Yoon strikes
right at mothers' hearts.

117
00:05:52,651 --> 00:05:55,254
(Laughter blooms
for 2-vote Ha Yoon and mom.)

118
00:05:55,254 --> 00:05:57,256
Mom, you weren't upset
when I got zero votes, right?

119
00:05:57,256 --> 00:06:00,359
I didn't feel bad,
but this feels really good.

120
00:06:00,659 --> 00:06:03,229
After revealing it all
and getting two votes,

121
00:06:03,829 --> 00:06:05,064
I feel amazing.

122
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,035
(High five)

123
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:11,570
I'm so glad I studied hard
because I listened to you.

124
00:06:11,570 --> 00:06:12,805
What a relief.

125
00:06:12,805 --> 00:06:15,141
See? Listen to your mom,
and good things happen.

126
00:06:15,141 --> 00:06:16,208
Exactly.

127
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:18,044
Cheers.

128
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:19,245
Cheers.

129
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:20,646
Get some sugar in you.

130
00:06:20,946 --> 00:06:23,149
This was the mothers' pick.

131
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:24,083
Right.

132
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:26,385
Don't forget that.

133
00:06:26,385 --> 00:06:28,154
From what I see,

134
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:31,590
if it had been the men's picks,
I'd never have gotten two votes.

135
00:06:33,192 --> 00:06:36,095
Do Yoon really surprised me.

136
00:06:36,362 --> 00:06:39,031
After hearing everyone's introductions,

137
00:06:39,031 --> 00:06:41,934
she was the most classic choice,
should I say?

138
00:06:42,535 --> 00:06:44,270
But from the mothers' perspective,

139
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:47,273
if she's young,
works at a major company, and is pretty,

140
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:49,709
isn't that good enough? It was surprising.

141
00:06:50,609 --> 00:06:53,579
Jeong Yoon is really pretty, right?

142
00:06:54,113 --> 00:06:56,115
She's your type, right? Her face.

143
00:06:56,115 --> 00:06:59,085
Honestly, just judging by looks,
age and such aside,

144
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:02,321
just looks-wise, she is exactly my type.

145
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:03,489
Right.

146
00:07:03,889 --> 00:07:06,192
But among Da Hye,
Ha Yoon, and Kang Hyeon...

147
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:10,863
I briefly talked with
all three of them yesterday.

148
00:07:10,863 --> 00:07:12,631
Wait, with Da Hye...

149
00:07:12,631 --> 00:07:13,733
Right.

150
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,234
- You didn't talk with Da Hye, did you?
- No.

151
00:07:15,234 --> 00:07:19,839
Keep track of it,
or you will get confused too.

152
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:21,974
Is that something you can track?

153
00:07:21,974 --> 00:07:23,943
Why track it? Why would you track it?

154
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:25,478
Why track that?

155
00:07:26,312 --> 00:07:27,813
(Ha Yoon, Ye Chan,
and Dong Young leave for their date.)

156
00:07:27,813 --> 00:07:29,849
How should we sit?

157
00:07:29,849 --> 00:07:31,183
- Would you like to sit in front?
- Ha Yoon, this way.

158
00:07:32,051 --> 00:07:34,186
Thank you.

159
00:07:34,186 --> 00:07:36,455
(Ha Yoon is escorted first.)

160
00:07:36,455 --> 00:07:38,391
- I'll close it.
- Yes, thank you.

161
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,027
Do you drive often?

162
00:07:41,027 --> 00:07:43,262
I drive for my commute.

163
00:07:43,262 --> 00:07:44,196
Really?

164
00:07:44,196 --> 00:07:45,598
Isn't it a bit cramped, Dong Young?

165
00:07:45,598 --> 00:07:47,867
- I'm fine.
- This side would be less cramped.

166
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:48,934
Wait.

167
00:07:49,168 --> 00:07:52,872
I've seen this scene a lot.

168
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:53,639
(Season 1 reference, Seung Hak sat
in the back and felt left out.)

169
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:54,974
This is a scene from Season One.

170
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:56,709
Seung Hak...

171
00:07:56,709 --> 00:07:58,044
You shouldn't sit in the back.

172
00:07:58,044 --> 00:07:59,645
sat in the back...

173
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:02,181
and seemed so pitiful.

174
00:08:03,449 --> 00:08:05,518
I've been driving for quite a while.
Over ten years, I think.

175
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:10,256
Then on your days off,
do you usually stay home?

176
00:08:10,256 --> 00:08:12,758
I like going around
trendy neighborhoods and cafés.

177
00:08:13,059 --> 00:08:14,860
Do you like saving places like that
and looking them up?

178
00:08:14,860 --> 00:08:15,895
Yes, I do.

179
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,297
When I see a few photos,

180
00:08:18,297 --> 00:08:20,499
I can tell,
"This place has to have a good vibe."

181
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:23,602
(The back seat can't join
the conversation.)

182
00:08:23,602 --> 00:08:26,772
It was a little disappointing
being in the back.

183
00:08:26,772 --> 00:08:28,874
I wanted to see Ha Yoon,

184
00:08:28,874 --> 00:08:32,745
and I wanted to talk to her directly,

185
00:08:32,745 --> 00:08:34,547
but I was sitting right behind her,

186
00:08:34,547 --> 00:08:37,950
so I couldn't really see her face,
which was such a shame.

187
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:39,452
I guess these are all
braised chicken restaurants.

188
00:08:39,452 --> 00:08:40,720
(Andong Market Jjimdak Alley)

189
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,955
- Andong braised chicken is good.
- There's a jjimdak alley.

190
00:08:42,955 --> 00:08:43,989
I'm hungry.

191
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:47,259
I will make sure
you get to know all about me today.

192
00:08:47,259 --> 00:08:48,094
That sounds good.

193
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:50,062
I think that would be nice.

194
00:08:50,062 --> 00:08:51,063
Then Ha Yoon,

195
00:08:51,063 --> 00:08:53,933
based on how you feel,

196
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:56,402
- What kind of person I find attractive?
- what kind of person attracts you?

197
00:08:56,402 --> 00:08:58,738
I like someone who leads first.

198
00:08:58,738 --> 00:09:00,573
Because...

199
00:09:00,573 --> 00:09:02,641
I'm the eldest daughter
in a Korean family,

200
00:09:02,641 --> 00:09:05,711
and I'm the head doctor at my clinic,

201
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:09,482
so I tend to have to lead
in every situation.

202
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:13,119
So when I'm dating,
someone who can lead me...

203
00:09:13,119 --> 00:09:15,521
makes my heart flutter a little more.

204
00:09:16,455 --> 00:09:18,858
Then on the other hand,

205
00:09:18,858 --> 00:09:21,827
since you seem very compatible
and accommodating,

206
00:09:21,827 --> 00:09:24,397
is there still anything
that's hard for you?

207
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:27,066
I'm sensitive to smells,

208
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,568
so smoking is hard for me.

209
00:09:29,568 --> 00:09:32,171
I'm also very sensitive to scents.

210
00:09:32,171 --> 00:09:33,172
Really?

211
00:09:33,172 --> 00:09:34,874
If you look at my desk,

212
00:09:34,874 --> 00:09:36,275
I have about 60 colognes.

213
00:09:36,275 --> 00:09:37,510
Sixty?

214
00:09:38,711 --> 00:09:40,246
- Are you a perfumer?
- No, nothing like that.

215
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,747
Isn't 60 a bit much?

216
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:44,817
I have this kind of hobby.

217
00:09:44,817 --> 00:09:48,354
I tried to appeal
with my sensitive sense of smell,

218
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:50,790
and mentioned that I own colognes,

219
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:54,527
that I have a collection.
That's what I mentioned.

220
00:09:54,527 --> 00:09:56,328
Could that be flirting?

221
00:09:56,328 --> 00:09:58,030
Perfume flirting.

222
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,965
The sauce seemed a bit dry.

223
00:09:59,965 --> 00:10:01,434
Thank you.

224
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:03,069
Thanks to you, it's nice and moist now.

225
00:10:06,338 --> 00:10:10,009
How many women
are both of you interested in?

226
00:10:10,409 --> 00:10:11,944
For me, about three so far.

227
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:15,147
We're only halfway through Day Two.

228
00:10:15,147 --> 00:10:17,616
I have about two,

229
00:10:17,616 --> 00:10:20,052
but I think I might narrow it down to one.

230
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,788
(Nod)

231
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:24,090
Did he rush it?

232
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:26,125
- He rushed it just now.
- He rushed it.

233
00:10:26,525 --> 00:10:27,493
Ye Chan doesn't need to rush.

234
00:10:27,493 --> 00:10:30,463
He just simply said, "There are three."

235
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:32,598
I think he said two
because he wanted fewer than three.

236
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:34,633
Then he rushed even more
and went down to one.

237
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:37,436
(Jeong Yoon, Shin Woo, and In Kwon's date)

238
00:10:37,436 --> 00:10:38,771
This place is known for its pasta.

239
00:10:40,573 --> 00:10:43,075
It really feels like a blind date.

240
00:10:43,442 --> 00:10:45,644
Who goes on a two-on-one blind date?

241
00:10:45,644 --> 00:10:48,247
- You must be very popular.
- Seriously.

242
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:50,082
Do you know how nervous the two of us are?

243
00:10:50,082 --> 00:10:52,518
I'm nervous too
because there are two of you.

244
00:10:52,518 --> 00:10:53,986
I'm twice as nervous.

245
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,321
I think you would be.

246
00:10:55,588 --> 00:10:57,990
What do you two usually do on days off?

247
00:10:57,990 --> 00:10:58,791
When I rest,

248
00:10:58,791 --> 00:11:01,927
I work out as a hobby
and like taking walks.

249
00:11:01,927 --> 00:11:03,429
I also like hiking.

250
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:05,498
You're really healthy.

251
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:07,600
I actually like games
more than you might think.

252
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,634
I play Teamfight Tactics,

253
00:11:08,634 --> 00:11:11,203
and I used to play Overwatch,

254
00:11:11,203 --> 00:11:13,439
and PUBG too. I liked games.

255
00:11:13,439 --> 00:11:15,941
Because I also worked
as an esports announcer.

256
00:11:15,941 --> 00:11:17,009
Do you play games?

257
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:19,011
Things like Teamfight Tactics...

258
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:20,880
- Do you play TFT?
- Yes.

259
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,181
You haven't tried this season yet, right?

260
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:23,949
I did. I played before I came here.

261
00:11:23,949 --> 00:11:26,385
You reached Emerald in that?

262
00:11:26,385 --> 00:11:29,021
No, it's too hard,
so I'm still figuring it out.

263
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:31,190
I think even while he's sitting there,

264
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:34,326
he's probably wondering
what Da Hye is doing.

265
00:11:34,326 --> 00:11:35,995
Really?

266
00:11:35,995 --> 00:11:38,664
I also like traveling
and things like that.

267
00:11:38,664 --> 00:11:41,534
While watching, I kept thinking
you looked like someone.

268
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:42,435
Who does she look like?

269
00:11:42,435 --> 00:11:44,036
Answer this right.

270
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:45,438
Who?

271
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:48,574
I think you look like Gong Seung Yeon.

272
00:11:48,574 --> 00:11:50,276
- You've heard that before, right?
- Really?

273
00:11:50,276 --> 00:11:52,778
I have heard it once or twice.

274
00:11:52,778 --> 00:11:55,114
I see.

275
00:11:56,248 --> 00:11:57,650
I can see the resemblance.

276
00:11:59,952 --> 00:12:01,921
I don't know what to do with myself.

277
00:12:01,921 --> 00:12:03,089
That's nice, though.

278
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:07,760
What do you two focus on
when dating women?

279
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:11,030
If I rank looks, personality, and ability,

280
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:13,466
it's personality, looks, ability.

281
00:12:13,466 --> 00:12:15,267
Personality, looks, ability.

282
00:12:15,835 --> 00:12:20,973
For me, it's looks, personality, ability.

283
00:12:20,973 --> 00:12:23,142
Then what kind of looks do you like?

284
00:12:23,142 --> 00:12:24,510
Gong Seung Yeon.

285
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:25,544
That was unexpected.

286
00:12:26,112 --> 00:12:27,179
Gong Seung Yeon.

287
00:12:29,682 --> 00:12:31,550
That was an unexpected flirt.

288
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:33,486
He builds it up so well.

289
00:12:34,387 --> 00:12:36,322
And he says it so calmly
without changing expression.

290
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:37,256
Exactly.

291
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:40,059
I think he dropped that line
very cleverly.

292
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,262
You have a clear physical type.

293
00:12:43,262 --> 00:12:48,467
Yes. There aren't many female celebrities
I follow on social media.

294
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:50,469
Really?

295
00:12:51,404 --> 00:12:55,541
I thought you were joking
when you said that.

296
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:57,410
It wasn't a joke. It was flirting...

297
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:58,411
in my own way.

298
00:12:58,411 --> 00:13:00,946
I suddenly couldn't remember the word.
Flirting, yes.

299
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,615
My goodness.

300
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,583
That's a good line.

301
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:06,986
I was a bit flustered, but I felt good.

302
00:13:06,986 --> 00:13:09,955
What woman wouldn't like being told
she resembles a pretty celebrity?

303
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:13,926
I asked about his ideal type next, and
he said that celebrity was his ideal type,

304
00:13:13,926 --> 00:13:17,530
so I thought, "He is very direct."

305
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:20,399
It made me wonder
what kind of person he is.

306
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:25,671
I really did muster up courage
and show it.

307
00:13:25,671 --> 00:13:28,674
It was my boldest flirt of 2026.

308
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:33,446
In Kwon was originally all about Do Yoon
from the first impression.

309
00:13:33,446 --> 00:13:36,816
Through this, do you think
he has changed to Jeong Yoon?

310
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:38,384
I think he's changed.

311
00:13:39,251 --> 00:13:41,787
(Jeong Yoon's team moves to a café.)

312
00:13:41,787 --> 00:13:44,357
This is really nice.

313
00:13:44,357 --> 00:13:45,524
It's really nice.

314
00:13:45,524 --> 00:13:48,461
Going out on dates really is nice.

315
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:49,628
I'm so glad I came.

316
00:13:49,628 --> 00:13:51,063
(The lush Andong scenery
unfolds like a painting.)

317
00:13:52,398 --> 00:13:53,999
Jeong Yoon,

318
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,335
if you were dating someone,
when would you want to marry?

319
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:58,804
I feel like even now, the timing is tight.

320
00:13:58,804 --> 00:14:02,408
So next year or the year after.
Next year would be even better.

321
00:14:03,376 --> 00:14:06,045
There are practical conditions, right?

322
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:08,147
How you want to handle housing,

323
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:09,682
whether it has to be a certain size,

324
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:11,550
whether it has to be in Seoul.
Things like that.

325
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,686
What do you think about those?

326
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:17,156
I would prefer not monthly rent,
but a lump-sum deposit lease, at least.

327
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:18,824
Does location not matter, then?

328
00:14:18,824 --> 00:14:20,893
Do you have age limits, older or younger?

329
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:23,596
What matters most
if you share common interests?

330
00:14:23,963 --> 00:14:26,232
He has a lot of questions.

331
00:14:26,232 --> 00:14:29,568
Is he asking all that
to make her lose interest?

332
00:14:29,568 --> 00:14:31,837
Is that why he's bombarding her
with questions?

333
00:14:31,837 --> 00:14:34,173
- I thought he was an MC.
- Why so many questions?

334
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:38,110
What if someone is very busy
but fairly capable?

335
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:39,445
What would you think of that?

336
00:14:39,945 --> 00:14:43,215
He should have some free time.
I'd like him to have some.

337
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,650
I really hated it.

338
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,285
There wasn't enough time,

339
00:14:46,285 --> 00:14:49,689
so even a one-on-one conversation
wouldn't have been enough,

340
00:14:49,989 --> 00:14:51,691
but with one more person there,

341
00:14:51,691 --> 00:14:52,892
it was very uncomfortable.

342
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:57,697
Even in a short time,
I thought getting to know the person...

343
00:14:57,697 --> 00:14:59,832
was basic courtesy in that situation,

344
00:14:59,832 --> 00:15:02,201
so I asked a lot of serious questions.

345
00:15:02,535 --> 00:15:05,171
There were no moments
that made my heart flutter,

346
00:15:05,171 --> 00:15:09,241
and I thought,
"What would Da Hye have done?"

347
00:15:09,975 --> 00:15:12,878
I get that, but don't do that to Da Hye.

348
00:15:12,878 --> 00:15:15,247
Right. He kept thinking about Da Hye.

349
00:15:15,881 --> 00:15:18,250
Seong Mo has gone there now.
He is a strong rival.

350
00:15:19,185 --> 00:15:21,787
(Da Hye and Seong Mo's date)

351
00:15:21,787 --> 00:15:22,855
Good work today.

352
00:15:22,855 --> 00:15:23,823
Thank you.

353
00:15:24,957 --> 00:15:29,495
(Slightly awkward)

354
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:32,531
But what's really amazing is,

355
00:15:32,531 --> 00:15:36,535
I really prefer talking
while looking into someone's eyes.

356
00:15:36,535 --> 00:15:37,570
Eyes.

357
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:39,238
But this feels like too much pressure.

358
00:15:39,238 --> 00:15:42,141
Please close them just a little.
Your eyes are too big.

359
00:15:43,109 --> 00:15:44,744
That's a good thing.
Because you look into my eyes well.

360
00:15:44,744 --> 00:15:47,279
But since you said it feels too intense,
I keep wanting to look away.

361
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,447
No, you can look.

362
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:49,615
Let's just have a staring contest, then.

363
00:15:50,816 --> 00:15:52,418
You can look.

364
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:54,253
What I am curious about here is this.

365
00:15:55,254 --> 00:15:58,424
When you're dating
and looking for someone to marry,

366
00:15:58,424 --> 00:16:00,526
do you really have no preferences at all?

367
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:04,363
I like cute and kind people...

368
00:16:04,363 --> 00:16:06,599
with bright, sparkling eyes.

369
00:16:06,599 --> 00:16:07,600
I see.

370
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:12,204
And I think I disliked people
who talked too much.

371
00:16:12,204 --> 00:16:17,143
I'd rather they be quiet.

372
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:20,179
Do I talk a lot?

373
00:16:20,179 --> 00:16:21,981
I haven't only talked about myself,
have I?

374
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,883
So far, you've only talked about yourself.

375
00:16:23,883 --> 00:16:25,451
You haven't asked me a single question.

376
00:16:26,719 --> 00:16:28,054
- Really?
- Yes.

377
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,056
I thought this was your self-pitch time.

378
00:16:31,924 --> 00:16:33,793
- You joke around well.
- Of course.

379
00:16:33,793 --> 00:16:35,895
They don't seem to click.

380
00:16:36,195 --> 00:16:38,531
I'm joking, to help you relax.

381
00:16:42,635 --> 00:16:46,038
She smiled and laughed a lot overall.

382
00:16:46,038 --> 00:16:48,174
So I think I felt fairly comfortable.

383
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:49,442
I was nervous too, though.

384
00:16:49,442 --> 00:16:50,543
Really?

385
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:52,978
I was very comfortable.

386
00:16:52,978 --> 00:16:55,581
With Seong Mo, I did think,

387
00:16:55,581 --> 00:16:57,416
"Wouldn't there be someone
who suits him better than me?"

388
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:00,886
(Meanwhile, at the lodging)

389
00:17:01,287 --> 00:17:02,855
I don't think Jeong Yoon's mother
has anything to be sad about.

390
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:05,024
- Don't say that.
- Men are lining up for your daughter.

391
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:07,226
Yesterday, they were all taken from us.

392
00:17:07,893 --> 00:17:09,462
There was a Korean medicine doctor.

393
00:17:09,462 --> 00:17:10,696
Right.

394
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,698
That was a total twist.

395
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,633
A landslide for
the Korean medicine doctor, right?

396
00:17:15,101 --> 00:17:17,169
(The mother of the Korean medicine doctor
with 2 votes joins.)

397
00:17:17,169 --> 00:17:19,338
Welcome,
mother of the Korean medicine doctor.

398
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:22,508
A landslide.

399
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:24,176
You made up
for yesterday's zero-vote heartbreak.

400
00:17:24,176 --> 00:17:25,444
I know.

401
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:27,046
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

402
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:28,714
What were you worried about?

403
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:29,882
You never know.

404
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:32,318
I couldn't eat anything.

405
00:17:32,318 --> 00:17:33,986
- So I'll eat first.
- Sure.

406
00:17:33,986 --> 00:17:36,122
Ms. Kim, should I make you a strong glass?

407
00:17:36,122 --> 00:17:36,989
You're so thoughtful.

408
00:17:36,989 --> 00:17:38,824
You just make it like this,

409
00:17:38,824 --> 00:17:41,794
then add water, so it's very simple.

410
00:17:41,794 --> 00:17:43,496
It's like roasted grain powder.

411
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:45,931
It dissolves really well in water too.

412
00:17:45,931 --> 00:17:46,932
It does.

413
00:17:46,932 --> 00:17:49,135
It's really easy to mix and drink.

414
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:51,370
It is filling enough to replace a meal.

415
00:17:51,370 --> 00:17:52,938
Thank you.

416
00:17:53,672 --> 00:17:56,876
(A hearty sip,
as filling as her vote count)

417
00:17:58,411 --> 00:17:59,211
It's good.

418
00:17:59,211 --> 00:18:00,413
- Is it good?
- Yes.

419
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:02,014
You're headed to the lodging
at the top, right?

420
00:18:02,014 --> 00:18:03,282
Yes, another long climb.

421
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:11,957
My goodness.

422
00:18:11,957 --> 00:18:13,159
Why?

423
00:18:13,159 --> 00:18:15,027
Both of them are so nice.

424
00:18:15,027 --> 00:18:16,095
Really?

425
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:17,963
I think Dong Young is better
at taking care of me.

426
00:18:17,963 --> 00:18:20,266
First, the one whose consideration
feels ingrained.

427
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:23,002
Opening the car door and serving food,

428
00:18:23,002 --> 00:18:25,805
things like that,
Dong Young seems a bit better at.

429
00:18:26,138 --> 00:18:27,373
But...

430
00:18:28,808 --> 00:18:31,744
the one who knows
what makes women flutter...

431
00:18:31,744 --> 00:18:32,978
seems to be Ye Chan.

432
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:36,449
- "The one who makes me flutter more..."
- Your heart has to move.

433
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:37,950
"is Ye Chan." That's what she's saying.

434
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,151
She's drawn to Ye Chan.

435
00:18:39,151 --> 00:18:41,287
Once she says all that
and then says "but,"

436
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:43,556
everything before that was unnecessary.

437
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,692
How was Ha Yoon?

438
00:18:46,692 --> 00:18:48,027
If I tell you what I think,

439
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,697
among the three people
I'm interested in now,

440
00:18:51,697 --> 00:18:53,099
Ha Yoon isn't one of them.

441
00:18:53,099 --> 00:18:54,667
As expected.

442
00:18:54,667 --> 00:18:59,138
He is someone with very firm opinions.

443
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:00,873
I'm more curious about the other three.

444
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:02,842
I can guess the three.

445
00:19:02,842 --> 00:19:05,878
Do Yoon, Da Hye, Jeong Yoon.

446
00:19:05,878 --> 00:19:06,846
Yes, that's right.

447
00:19:07,613 --> 00:19:08,714
Right?

448
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:12,017
Ha Yoon is really great
once you experience her, right?

449
00:19:12,017 --> 00:19:13,586
She's even better than expected.

450
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,722
The more you talk to her,

451
00:19:17,556 --> 00:19:19,325
the more everyone realizes
how good Ha Yoon is.

452
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:21,894
They all notice, yes.

453
00:19:21,894 --> 00:19:25,798
After talking to Ha Yoon,
we realized she was good too.

454
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:32,138
It would be great
if our hearts truly connected.

455
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,841
At a glance, she really seems...

456
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:37,576
like she would suit
my eldest daughter-in-law.

457
00:19:37,576 --> 00:19:38,744
With my sister-in-law?

458
00:19:38,744 --> 00:19:40,312
Right. With my sister-in-law too,

459
00:19:40,312 --> 00:19:42,648
- I think they would get along well.
- Already?

460
00:19:42,948 --> 00:19:44,817
I think the atmosphere
would get even better.

461
00:19:44,817 --> 00:19:45,818
Exactly.

462
00:19:46,085 --> 00:19:47,153
Was it hard?

463
00:19:47,987 --> 00:19:49,155
Was it not fun?

464
00:19:49,755 --> 00:19:51,924
Maybe because I was so nervous.

465
00:19:53,726 --> 00:19:56,295
(Flop)

466
00:19:56,662 --> 00:19:58,264
I don't know what I even said.

467
00:19:58,264 --> 00:19:59,432
I guess Seong Mo felt drained.

468
00:19:59,432 --> 00:20:01,233
I think I even lied.

469
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:02,301
Lied?

470
00:20:02,301 --> 00:20:03,335
Were you out of it?

471
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:05,571
It doesn't even feel like I ate.

472
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:07,573
She is nice,

473
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:09,742
but "I should date this person"...

474
00:20:09,742 --> 00:20:12,912
does not come to mind. Why is that?

475
00:20:13,646 --> 00:20:15,614
That's why you're getting
to know everyone now.

476
00:20:15,614 --> 00:20:17,116
To feel that
after seeing someone once isn't...

477
00:20:17,116 --> 00:20:19,085
- Right?
- Of course.

478
00:20:19,085 --> 00:20:23,389
If you're a decent man yourself,
you can date them.

479
00:20:24,924 --> 00:20:26,559
A two-on-one really is not easy.

480
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:28,294
Right, they were saying that earlier.

481
00:20:30,096 --> 00:20:31,630
Still, I think I handled it cleanly.

482
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:32,932
Really? How was it?

483
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:34,533
The conversation flowed really well.

484
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:39,205
I like women like Jeong Yoon.

485
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:41,073
Someone who would build a good home.

486
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:43,776
She is a good person who suits you,

487
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:47,613
but you were a bit hesitant
because you are in the same field.

488
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:49,682
In terms of job,

489
00:20:50,449 --> 00:20:51,450
it was Do Yoon.

490
00:20:52,952 --> 00:20:54,086
It was Do Yoon,

491
00:20:55,454 --> 00:20:57,790
but after meeting
and talking to Jeong Yoon...

492
00:20:58,324 --> 00:20:59,625
If tonight they say again,

493
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:02,228
"Put the norigae
in the chest of the person you like,"

494
00:21:03,362 --> 00:21:04,697
I think I'll have to think about it.

495
00:21:04,697 --> 00:21:06,465
He's still wavering.

496
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,667
Well...

497
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:11,137
Why are you sighing? Was the date not fun?

498
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:13,205
Normally,

499
00:21:13,205 --> 00:21:15,374
when someone is pretty and you're drawn
to them, you get nervous, right?

500
00:21:16,342 --> 00:21:17,977
Yesterday, I was nervous,

501
00:21:17,977 --> 00:21:19,779
but today,
that kind of nervousness wasn't there.

502
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:23,149
But Jeong Yoon is beautiful.
She was Miss Korea.

503
00:21:23,149 --> 00:21:26,052
Right. Objectively, she is pretty.

504
00:21:26,719 --> 00:21:29,655
But I felt she was very different from me.

505
00:21:30,256 --> 00:21:33,125
Then you could complement each other well,

506
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:36,262
make up for each other's strengths
and weaknesses. That's good.

507
00:21:37,697 --> 00:21:40,599
What now?

508
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:42,702
So today,

509
00:21:42,702 --> 00:21:45,237
did you want to talk to Da Hye alone?

510
00:21:46,238 --> 00:21:48,441
You were fixed only on Da Hye.

511
00:21:48,874 --> 00:21:50,109
And still,

512
00:21:50,109 --> 00:21:52,011
the fact that I am fixed on her
has not changed.

513
00:21:52,011 --> 00:21:56,849
Once you get fixed on something,
you follow it through.

514
00:21:57,349 --> 00:21:58,951
You don't change easily.

515
00:21:58,951 --> 00:22:01,020
His mother doesn't like that.

516
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:02,855
If you were going to decide in one day,

517
00:22:02,855 --> 00:22:06,125
they would just make it
one night and two days.

518
00:22:06,125 --> 00:22:10,329
You're very rational
when it comes to studying and work,

519
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:12,031
but should I say
you have no eye for women?

520
00:22:13,065 --> 00:22:15,801
I do have an eye for women.

521
00:22:15,801 --> 00:22:18,170
You might be seeing only one side.

522
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:19,839
All I saw were good sides.

523
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,608
From what I see,

524
00:22:22,608 --> 00:22:24,810
his heart has already been stolen.

525
00:22:24,810 --> 00:22:27,413
His heart is leaning more toward Da Hye.

526
00:22:27,413 --> 00:22:28,547
Exactly.

527
00:22:30,649 --> 00:22:34,453
Contestants and mothers,
please move to Cheonjamun Yard.

528
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:35,955
Are we doing something else?

529
00:22:37,123 --> 00:22:38,357
I think we're doing something else.

530
00:22:38,357 --> 00:22:39,892
Is there another event?

531
00:22:39,892 --> 00:22:40,993
It seems like something's happening.

532
00:22:41,761 --> 00:22:44,230
What is going to happen now?

533
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:48,868
Contestants and mothers,

534
00:22:48,868 --> 00:22:52,905
please stand where the men's mothers
made their choices earlier today.

535
00:22:53,806 --> 00:22:56,675
I'm troubled. What is it this time?

536
00:22:56,675 --> 00:22:57,810
What are they trying to do?

537
00:22:58,411 --> 00:23:00,746
I don't want to relive that memory.

538
00:23:02,648 --> 00:23:05,117
I can't predict what they'll make us do.

539
00:23:05,117 --> 00:23:06,419
Yeah, exactly.

540
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:11,791
We will now
have the men's choice dinner date.

541
00:23:14,694 --> 00:23:16,495
Again?

542
00:23:16,495 --> 00:23:17,963
The men are choosing?

543
00:23:18,764 --> 00:23:22,635
Men, please move next to the woman
you want to date.

544
00:23:22,635 --> 00:23:25,171
This time, the men choose.

545
00:23:26,439 --> 00:23:27,606
What?

546
00:23:28,874 --> 00:23:29,909
This is bad.

547
00:23:30,543 --> 00:23:32,111
Da Hye was standing next to me,

548
00:23:32,111 --> 00:23:34,547
and my hand got hot and started sweating.

549
00:23:34,914 --> 00:23:36,816
I thought, "The moment has come."

550
00:23:37,917 --> 00:23:39,018
This is my chance.

551
00:23:40,019 --> 00:23:41,721
This is cruel.

552
00:23:41,721 --> 00:23:43,422
This really isn't easy.

553
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:47,760
I was hoping In Kwon would choose me.

554
00:23:49,128 --> 00:23:52,965
I think I just hoped
at least one person might come.

555
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:59,505
The person you had
a good daytime date with is beside you,

556
00:23:59,505 --> 00:24:02,141
and he could move somewhere else.

557
00:24:02,141 --> 00:24:04,610
That's also a really awkward situation.

558
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:06,045
The men must feel so stuck.

559
00:24:06,045 --> 00:24:09,515
If that happens,
it's the "Dong Young Situation" again.

560
00:24:11,217 --> 00:24:13,552
Moon Seong Mo will choose first.

561
00:24:13,552 --> 00:24:14,553
Moon Seong Mo.

562
00:24:16,055 --> 00:24:16,922
Are your hands sweating?

563
00:24:16,922 --> 00:24:18,758
- My hands are suddenly sweating a lot.
- You can do it.

564
00:24:20,159 --> 00:24:22,528
(Will he stay beside Kim Da Hye?)

565
00:24:22,528 --> 00:24:25,431
(Or will he move?)

566
00:24:25,931 --> 00:24:28,467
(Seong Mo takes a step first.)

567
00:24:29,435 --> 00:24:31,871
(Nervous)

568
00:24:32,738 --> 00:24:34,874
(Where will Seong Mo's steps lead?)

569
00:24:34,874 --> 00:24:36,342
- Is he acting?
- Where is he going?

570
00:24:36,809 --> 00:24:37,877
Do we let go of hands?

571
00:24:38,677 --> 00:24:39,678
Where is he going?

572
00:24:41,580 --> 00:24:45,484
(His first-impression pick, Kang Hyeon?)

573
00:24:46,552 --> 00:24:47,720
Where is he going?

574
00:24:49,188 --> 00:24:51,824
(He passes Lee Kang Hyeon.)

575
00:24:56,929 --> 00:24:58,864
He's going to Jeong Yoon.

576
00:25:01,033 --> 00:25:02,101
My gosh.

577
00:25:06,305 --> 00:25:08,174
Jeong Yoon.

578
00:25:08,808 --> 00:25:11,944
- His norigae vote was for Jeong Yoon too.
- It was for Jeong Yoon.

579
00:25:15,214 --> 00:25:16,415
What is going on?

580
00:25:17,116 --> 00:25:19,018
I thought, "Why did he come?"

581
00:25:19,018 --> 00:25:22,588
Because I thought
he had no interest in me at all.

582
00:25:23,289 --> 00:25:25,825
He suddenly came,
so I was really surprised.

583
00:25:26,859 --> 00:25:28,494
She didn't know
because it was a secret vote.

584
00:25:28,494 --> 00:25:32,098
Moon Seong Mo has been...

585
00:25:32,665 --> 00:25:34,667
- Jeong Yoon from the beginning until now.
- Right.

586
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:37,570
Ever since he had to make choices.

587
00:25:37,570 --> 00:25:39,572
The number six you mentioned...

588
00:25:39,572 --> 00:25:41,207
(At the first meeting table...)

589
00:25:41,207 --> 00:25:44,076
(and in the norigae vote too)

590
00:25:44,310 --> 00:25:48,180
He kept saying in interviews
that he liked Jeong Yoon.

591
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:49,982
But they never had time
to do anything together.

592
00:25:49,982 --> 00:25:51,484
Right. They had no time to talk.

593
00:25:51,951 --> 00:25:52,985
Three people.

594
00:25:53,819 --> 00:25:55,621
No, not yet...

595
00:25:55,621 --> 00:25:56,989
because only one person has moved.

596
00:25:58,524 --> 00:26:01,660
Jeong Yoon is so popular.

597
00:26:02,061 --> 00:26:03,229
Let us hug once before I go.

598
00:26:04,997 --> 00:26:05,898
(Tight hug)

599
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:06,899
Look at them.

600
00:26:10,102 --> 00:26:13,706
(The two mothers' heartfelt farewell)

601
00:26:15,207 --> 00:26:17,143
- Welcome.
- What do I do?

602
00:26:17,143 --> 00:26:18,944
There are so many here.

603
00:26:18,944 --> 00:26:21,814
Someone may change their mind.

604
00:26:29,455 --> 00:26:31,323
Kang Shin Woo, please choose next.

605
00:26:31,323 --> 00:26:32,558
Kang Shin Woo.

606
00:26:33,025 --> 00:26:37,329
Every season,
there are one or two people...

607
00:26:37,329 --> 00:26:39,699
whose choices are obvious
without even watching.

608
00:26:39,699 --> 00:26:42,902
I think this season, it's him.

609
00:26:43,536 --> 00:26:45,805
Kang Shin Woo, please choose next.

610
00:26:45,805 --> 00:26:48,674
(Will Shin Woo's choice be that obvious?)

611
00:26:49,442 --> 00:26:53,446
Even if he does not feel romantically
toward Jeong Yoon,

612
00:26:53,446 --> 00:26:55,181
after meeting her twice or three times,

613
00:26:55,181 --> 00:26:56,782
those feelings could develop.

614
00:26:56,782 --> 00:26:59,719
- His mother is totally set on Jeong Yoon.
- I wish he would meet her more.

615
00:27:03,489 --> 00:27:06,992
(Shin Woo immediately starts walking.)

616
00:27:07,226 --> 00:27:10,129
(Will he go straight to Da Hye again?)

617
00:27:10,496 --> 00:27:11,697
No.

618
00:27:11,697 --> 00:27:13,065
- Is he pretending to go?
- Will he turn?

619
00:27:13,065 --> 00:27:14,533
No, he's gone there.

620
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,102
Go quickly. Everyone already knows.

621
00:27:16,102 --> 00:27:17,770
Yes, exactly. It isn't that dramatic.

622
00:27:19,839 --> 00:27:21,073
Thank you.

623
00:27:21,974 --> 00:27:23,776
- Let's enjoy our meal.
- Yes.

624
00:27:23,776 --> 00:27:25,311
As expected, he goes to Da Hye.

625
00:27:25,311 --> 00:27:27,279
(Kang Shin Woo chooses Kim Da Hye.)

626
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:32,785
I guess I should let go of your hand.

627
00:27:33,552 --> 00:27:34,553
Goodbye.

628
00:27:35,621 --> 00:27:37,256
You're wearing pink today.

629
00:27:37,256 --> 00:27:38,057
Right?

630
00:27:38,524 --> 00:27:40,192
But black suits you well too.

631
00:27:40,192 --> 00:27:41,327
There is BLACKPINK, you know.

632
00:27:41,327 --> 00:27:42,294
BLACKPINK.

633
00:27:42,294 --> 00:27:43,696
His face is pink now.

634
00:27:45,931 --> 00:27:47,700
I'm flustered too...

635
00:27:47,700 --> 00:27:50,569
because I think I've fallen
too hard for Da Hye.

636
00:27:50,569 --> 00:27:53,939
I thought simply spending time with her
would be wonderful,

637
00:27:53,939 --> 00:27:56,242
so I chose Kim Da Hye.

638
00:27:58,377 --> 00:28:03,616
(Leaving her favorite potential in-law)

639
00:28:03,616 --> 00:28:06,052
- We meet again.
- We meet again.

640
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:07,953
Nice to see you.

641
00:28:07,953 --> 00:28:09,555
(He moves next to Da Hye's mother.)

642
00:28:10,556 --> 00:28:11,824
Shin Woo...

643
00:28:11,824 --> 00:28:13,893
seems like a very direct man.

644
00:28:13,893 --> 00:28:16,696
He values first impressions a lot,

645
00:28:16,696 --> 00:28:20,800
and he seemed interested only in Da Hye.

646
00:28:22,535 --> 00:28:24,770
Kim Dong Young, please choose next.

647
00:28:30,976 --> 00:28:35,848
(Ha Yoon lover,
Will mom and son's hearts match?)

648
00:28:36,148 --> 00:28:37,349
I guess he'll stay.

649
00:28:44,056 --> 00:28:45,024
I've chosen.

650
00:28:48,594 --> 00:28:49,862
(Kim Dong Young chooses Yang Ha Yoon.)

651
00:28:49,862 --> 00:28:50,796
Thank you.

652
00:28:53,799 --> 00:28:54,700
My heart fluttered.

653
00:28:55,568 --> 00:28:56,602
He's a man.

654
00:28:58,704 --> 00:29:02,074
It seemed he was a manly man.

655
00:29:03,042 --> 00:29:05,010
I told you he would make it someday.

656
00:29:06,412 --> 00:29:08,314
I said I thought he would make it.

657
00:29:09,448 --> 00:29:13,452
(Dong Young chooses Ha Yoon,
same as his mother.)

658
00:29:13,452 --> 00:29:14,653
He's charming.

659
00:29:15,654 --> 00:29:18,858
He's really direct.

660
00:29:18,858 --> 00:29:20,493
He's very manly.

661
00:29:20,493 --> 00:29:22,028
Her mother's heart fluttered too.

662
00:29:22,028 --> 00:29:25,498
I really like that part of him.

663
00:29:25,998 --> 00:29:28,067
It's because we haven't talked
one-on-one, right?

664
00:29:28,067 --> 00:29:29,301
Yes.

665
00:29:29,301 --> 00:29:30,836
That was what I regretted most.

666
00:29:31,504 --> 00:29:32,872
I have things I want to say...

667
00:29:32,872 --> 00:29:33,839
Really?

668
00:29:34,373 --> 00:29:35,875
and things I want to tell you.

669
00:29:35,875 --> 00:29:36,876
Really?

670
00:29:37,610 --> 00:29:39,245
That expression looks excited.

671
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:43,449
Kwon Ye Chan, please choose next.

672
00:29:44,583 --> 00:29:46,886
I'm curious about Ye Chan's choice.

673
00:29:46,886 --> 00:29:48,487
Maybe Kwon Ye Chan will stay
where he is too.

674
00:29:49,955 --> 00:29:51,490
(Ye Chan leaves the spot beside Ha Yoon.)

675
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:52,425
He's leaving.

676
00:29:55,261 --> 00:30:01,600
(Where will Ye Chan head?)

677
00:30:03,736 --> 00:30:06,839
I think his first choice
would be Jeong Yoon.

678
00:30:06,839 --> 00:30:09,241
His second would be Da Hye.

679
00:30:17,917 --> 00:30:19,051
Thank you.

680
00:30:19,051 --> 00:30:20,953
(Kwon Ye Chan chooses Ahn Do Yoon.)

681
00:30:20,953 --> 00:30:23,122
That is an excellent choice.

682
00:30:23,756 --> 00:30:29,161
This is when Do Yoon would feel bad.

683
00:30:29,161 --> 00:30:31,497
She could not go out on a date that day.

684
00:30:31,497 --> 00:30:33,332
It could be heartbreaking.

685
00:30:33,332 --> 00:30:35,067
Then someone she did not expect,

686
00:30:35,067 --> 00:30:39,605
and even someone quite popular,
comes to her.

687
00:30:39,605 --> 00:30:41,574
So her interest could shoot right up.

688
00:30:41,574 --> 00:30:43,542
So timing like this is very important.

689
00:30:44,243 --> 00:30:45,344
Yes.

690
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:48,247
Nice to see you.

691
00:30:48,247 --> 00:30:49,582
Thank you.

692
00:30:52,251 --> 00:30:53,219
This feels nice.

693
00:30:55,020 --> 00:30:56,555
This feels strange.

694
00:30:57,823 --> 00:30:59,959
No, you have to go now.

695
00:30:59,959 --> 00:31:01,127
Do I have to?

696
00:31:01,127 --> 00:31:03,596
You should.
Hurry over to Do Yoon's mother.

697
00:31:04,597 --> 00:31:05,664
Come this way.

698
00:31:06,098 --> 00:31:07,466
(Ye Chan's mother also moves.)

699
00:31:07,466 --> 00:31:08,534
A savior.

700
00:31:10,202 --> 00:31:11,637
Thank you so much.

701
00:31:11,637 --> 00:31:13,906
- Not at all.
- I thought I would get zero votes again.

702
00:31:14,774 --> 00:31:17,143
Because I was not picked by the mothers,

703
00:31:17,143 --> 00:31:21,047
I was just very grateful
that Ye Chan came to me...

704
00:31:21,047 --> 00:31:22,248
first.

705
00:31:22,248 --> 00:31:23,849
After hearing about her from her mother,

706
00:31:23,849 --> 00:31:25,785
even though she is the youngest,

707
00:31:25,785 --> 00:31:30,056
without any leave of absence or break,

708
00:31:30,056 --> 00:31:33,025
she seemed to have lived
very passionately.

709
00:31:33,025 --> 00:31:36,696
So I strongly felt I should talk with her.

710
00:31:37,029 --> 00:31:39,065
How tall is Do Yoon?

711
00:31:39,065 --> 00:31:42,768
Do Yoon is just under 170 cm.

712
00:31:43,069 --> 00:31:44,837
Their heights match well too.

713
00:31:44,837 --> 00:31:46,238
She's tall too.

714
00:31:47,673 --> 00:31:50,810
Lastly, Lee In Kwon, please choose.

715
00:31:52,578 --> 00:31:55,948
In Kwon has to choose well here.

716
00:31:57,116 --> 00:31:59,819
Kang Hyeon still has zero votes.

717
00:32:04,156 --> 00:32:07,860
I did hope someone would go to her.

718
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:14,767
Right now, the person I still like is...

719
00:32:14,767 --> 00:32:15,735
Jeong Yoon.

720
00:32:16,569 --> 00:32:18,471
In Kwon...

721
00:32:18,471 --> 00:32:20,539
might be interested in Do Yoon.

722
00:32:20,539 --> 00:32:22,174
I feel like he'll go to Do Yoon.

723
00:32:22,975 --> 00:32:24,176
He has to choose well.

724
00:32:24,844 --> 00:32:27,012
In Kwon isn't moving.

725
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,982
I don't want a two-on-one date.

726
00:32:30,783 --> 00:32:32,718
Go over there.

727
00:32:33,219 --> 00:32:34,453
Go over there.

728
00:32:37,189 --> 00:32:38,391
I've chosen.

729
00:32:39,525 --> 00:32:41,027
(Lee In Kwon chooses Choi Jeong Yoon.)

730
00:32:41,027 --> 00:32:42,895
He didn't go.

731
00:32:43,329 --> 00:32:46,332
I stayed with Choi Jeong Yoon.

732
00:32:46,932 --> 00:32:50,669
I had a lot of regret from the lunch date,

733
00:32:50,669 --> 00:32:53,572
and I wanted to quench that thirst.

734
00:32:54,707 --> 00:32:58,644
(But another two-on-one date
is confirmed.)

735
00:32:59,111 --> 00:33:02,848
(Men's choice date matches are complete.)

736
00:33:03,616 --> 00:33:05,051
(Lee Kang Hyeon, 0 votes)

737
00:33:05,051 --> 00:33:06,652
- Goodness.
- Goodness.

738
00:33:08,454 --> 00:33:10,256
Her mother must be heartbroken.

739
00:33:12,725 --> 00:33:14,293
Mom, I think we should leave.

740
00:33:19,899 --> 00:33:23,135
It would be strange to say I felt nothing.

741
00:33:23,569 --> 00:33:27,039
I felt sorry for Kang Hyeon and upset too.

742
00:33:28,307 --> 00:33:30,743
Since it happened three times in a row,

743
00:33:30,743 --> 00:33:33,412
I hoped someone would go
to Kang Hyeon tonight.

744
00:33:33,412 --> 00:33:35,014
I had that hope.

745
00:33:35,014 --> 00:33:37,783
Up to two times was okay,
but the third time was a bit much.

746
00:33:39,318 --> 00:33:40,753
I thought we should leave,

747
00:33:41,554 --> 00:33:44,256
that we should pack our bags.

748
00:33:47,293 --> 00:33:49,161
It is disappointing, but what can you do?
Life is like that.

749
00:33:50,696 --> 00:33:55,434
Kang Hyeon got zero votes again.

750
00:33:55,434 --> 00:34:00,106
At first, because I was a little worried,

751
00:34:00,506 --> 00:34:04,777
I nagged a bit.

752
00:34:05,211 --> 00:34:09,382
But now, as time goes by,
I feel sorry for her.

753
00:34:09,382 --> 00:34:10,750
I'm upset too.

754
00:34:10,750 --> 00:34:13,352
Her mother is watching
all of this with her.

755
00:34:13,352 --> 00:34:14,553
Exactly.

756
00:34:14,553 --> 00:34:16,222
It's not just once.

757
00:34:16,222 --> 00:34:18,624
The first, second, and third rounds
were all zero votes.

758
00:34:20,359 --> 00:34:24,063
(Night falls over the lodge.)

759
00:34:24,897 --> 00:34:26,932
(In different spaces,)

760
00:34:26,932 --> 00:34:33,739
(the men wait for their dates.)

761
00:34:36,108 --> 00:34:37,777
- Hello.
- Hello.

762
00:34:38,210 --> 00:34:40,679
(Ye Chan's date Do Yoon appears.)

763
00:34:40,679 --> 00:34:41,814
Please sit comfortably.

764
00:34:43,516 --> 00:34:45,584
This is a one-on-one date, right?

765
00:34:45,584 --> 00:34:46,786
It looks delicious.

766
00:34:46,786 --> 00:34:47,853
Did you wait long?

767
00:34:47,853 --> 00:34:49,755
No. I just got here too.

768
00:34:51,223 --> 00:34:53,192
- Please eat while we talk.
- Yes, let us eat.

769
00:34:54,727 --> 00:34:55,494
(Have some.)

770
00:34:55,494 --> 00:34:56,362
Thank you.

771
00:34:57,063 --> 00:34:58,431
Should I set yours down too?

772
00:34:58,431 --> 00:34:59,465
Equally.

773
00:34:59,465 --> 00:35:00,332
Thank you.

774
00:35:03,769 --> 00:35:05,171
You were busy all day, right?

775
00:35:06,272 --> 00:35:08,207
I did not do much,
but time went by so quickly.

776
00:35:09,375 --> 00:35:11,677
You heard the women's introductions today.

777
00:35:11,677 --> 00:35:13,746
How was it after hearing my introduction?

778
00:35:15,114 --> 00:35:16,348
First, after hearing your introduction,

779
00:35:17,516 --> 00:35:18,484
I thought...

780
00:35:19,819 --> 00:35:23,522
for someone your age,
you seemed to have lived...

781
00:35:25,558 --> 00:35:28,527
very diligently and passionately.

782
00:35:28,928 --> 00:35:30,696
So I really wanted to have
a one-on-one talk.

783
00:35:34,867 --> 00:35:36,502
Then how many years have you worked there?

784
00:35:36,502 --> 00:35:38,070
I'm in my fifth year.

785
00:35:39,105 --> 00:35:40,806
You must take pride in working there.

786
00:35:40,806 --> 00:35:41,841
Me?

787
00:35:42,541 --> 00:35:46,846
I was curious about how you got in,

788
00:35:46,846 --> 00:35:47,847
and I wanted to hear your story.

789
00:35:47,847 --> 00:35:49,048
I got in...

790
00:35:49,048 --> 00:35:51,450
because my major
was electronic engineering.

791
00:35:51,450 --> 00:35:52,952
Really?

792
00:35:52,952 --> 00:35:55,087
She must have been popular in college.

793
00:35:55,087 --> 00:35:56,155
Exactly.

794
00:35:56,722 --> 00:35:58,257
I am...

795
00:35:58,257 --> 00:36:00,159
the complete opposite.

796
00:36:00,159 --> 00:36:01,160
Were you a liberal arts major?

797
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,795
- You cannot say it yet.
- It is hard to say in that regard.

798
00:36:02,795 --> 00:36:05,664
This is a little tricky
because I haven't introduced myself yet.

799
00:36:06,098 --> 00:36:08,667
What do you think about age gaps?

800
00:36:08,667 --> 00:36:10,436
When I go on blind dates outside,

801
00:36:10,436 --> 00:36:13,272
I say up to six years is okay.

802
00:36:13,272 --> 00:36:15,007
Is there a specific reason for six years?

803
00:36:15,674 --> 00:36:17,443
Because seven years feels...

804
00:36:17,443 --> 00:36:19,512
like it's close to ten.

805
00:36:19,512 --> 00:36:20,346
As expected,

806
00:36:20,813 --> 00:36:22,181
an engineering approach.

807
00:36:22,181 --> 00:36:23,349
Maybe so.

808
00:36:23,349 --> 00:36:26,018
Seven is a bit much, but six is okay.

809
00:36:26,018 --> 00:36:28,454
Anything before that is okay.

810
00:36:29,088 --> 00:36:30,990
So up to six years is okay,

811
00:36:30,990 --> 00:36:31,957
but also,

812
00:36:31,957 --> 00:36:33,793
- I like older men.
- Really?

813
00:36:33,793 --> 00:36:37,363
Until now, among younger, older,
and same age, which did you prefer?

814
00:36:37,363 --> 00:36:40,700
I think I have dated older and younger...

815
00:36:40,700 --> 00:36:42,101
and same-age people all fairly similarly.

816
00:36:42,101 --> 00:36:43,436
- You've dated older women too?
- Yes.

817
00:36:43,436 --> 00:36:44,603
Really?

818
00:36:45,337 --> 00:36:46,372
Because, well,

819
00:36:46,372 --> 00:36:48,674
I was younger at one point too.

820
00:36:48,674 --> 00:36:51,077
Back then,
older didn't feel that much older.

821
00:36:51,077 --> 00:36:54,747
You seem very mature to me,

822
00:36:54,747 --> 00:36:57,616
so I get the feeling
you were popular with younger women.

823
00:36:58,551 --> 00:37:00,052
- Maybe I was.
- Right?

824
00:37:01,687 --> 00:37:03,055
I think you would've been.

825
00:37:03,055 --> 00:37:05,124
Talking with Ye Chan was fun,

826
00:37:05,124 --> 00:37:07,159
and my interest in him went way up.

827
00:37:07,159 --> 00:37:09,362
He is mature,

828
00:37:09,362 --> 00:37:11,864
and I like someone who tends to lead.

829
00:37:11,864 --> 00:37:13,599
He had that kind of energy.

830
00:37:13,599 --> 00:37:16,535
I think I started to feel
a little romantic spark.

831
00:37:18,237 --> 00:37:19,538
(Two-on-one date
with Jeong Yoon and two men)

832
00:37:19,538 --> 00:37:21,741
- You're here.
- The menu is chicken.

833
00:37:22,408 --> 00:37:24,009
Things are intense here.

834
00:37:24,009 --> 00:37:24,844
I know.

835
00:37:24,844 --> 00:37:25,845
Two men.

836
00:37:26,312 --> 00:37:28,848
Do you prefer bone-in or boneless?

837
00:37:28,848 --> 00:37:30,716
I eat both well,

838
00:37:30,716 --> 00:37:33,853
but here, boneless,
since I can eat it neatly.

839
00:37:37,890 --> 00:37:41,260
What did your mother say
about you eating with two men again?

840
00:37:41,260 --> 00:37:45,498
Since it is still Day Two
and I am meeting new people,

841
00:37:45,498 --> 00:37:48,134
she was actually a little worried...

842
00:37:48,134 --> 00:37:50,302
that I would not be able
to have deep conversations.

843
00:37:51,037 --> 00:37:52,238
You've talked to everyone now, right?

844
00:37:52,238 --> 00:37:53,172
Yes, now.

845
00:37:53,172 --> 00:37:56,075
Because I hadn't talked
with you at all, Seong Mo.

846
00:37:56,075 --> 00:37:58,844
I think we almost never spoke.

847
00:37:59,412 --> 00:38:00,913
You live in Hak-dong, right?

848
00:38:01,313 --> 00:38:04,083
I live right in front of
Gangnam-gu Office Station.

849
00:38:04,583 --> 00:38:06,385
How long have you lived alone?

850
00:38:06,385 --> 00:38:09,221
I have lived alone
since I was 20, so 11 years.

851
00:38:09,789 --> 00:38:11,357
And you've had your dog for seven years?

852
00:38:11,357 --> 00:38:12,992
About seven or eight years.

853
00:38:12,992 --> 00:38:14,326
I have a dog too.

854
00:38:14,326 --> 00:38:15,695
- Really?
- At my family home.

855
00:38:16,262 --> 00:38:17,363
(An unexpected common point)

856
00:38:17,363 --> 00:38:18,431
What breed?

857
00:38:18,431 --> 00:38:19,532
Toy poodle.

858
00:38:19,532 --> 00:38:23,169
It must be cute.
My family home has a poodle too.

859
00:38:23,169 --> 00:38:25,071
I like poodles best.

860
00:38:25,071 --> 00:38:27,239
I only raise curly-haired dogs too.

861
00:38:27,239 --> 00:38:28,574
They don't shed much.

862
00:38:28,574 --> 00:38:30,142
Bichons are similar.

863
00:38:30,142 --> 00:38:31,043
They don't shed?

864
00:38:31,043 --> 00:38:33,512
Bichons are curly too,
and they don't shed.

865
00:38:33,512 --> 00:38:35,014
- I guess he doesn't have a dog.
- I guess not.

866
00:38:35,014 --> 00:38:36,682
Bichons are sturdier...

867
00:38:36,682 --> 00:38:39,885
because their legs are thick,
so their kneecaps are stronger.

868
00:38:39,885 --> 00:38:41,087
Compared to poodles.

869
00:38:41,087 --> 00:38:43,656
Poodles are kind of the default.

870
00:38:43,656 --> 00:38:45,725
There was a moment
when I was completely left out.

871
00:38:45,725 --> 00:38:48,094
I don't have a pet,

872
00:38:48,728 --> 00:38:50,730
but both of them had raised pets
for a long time.

873
00:38:51,263 --> 00:38:52,998
It felt awkward to join a conversation
I knew nothing about.

874
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:56,969
Even worse than lunch,

875
00:38:56,969 --> 00:38:58,137
it was bad.

876
00:38:58,838 --> 00:39:00,973
Chicken and beer? I'm so excited.

877
00:39:00,973 --> 00:39:02,308
- Do you like chicken and beer?
- Yes.

878
00:39:03,309 --> 00:39:06,145
(Dong Young and Ha Yoon's one-on-one date)

879
00:39:06,145 --> 00:39:09,648
Ha Yoon and Dong Young
finally have a one-on-one date.

880
00:39:10,182 --> 00:39:13,753
Earlier, you gave me a teaser.

881
00:39:13,753 --> 00:39:14,820
So you came looking forward to it, right?

882
00:39:14,820 --> 00:39:16,322
- Yes, I was so curious.
- Right.

883
00:39:17,189 --> 00:39:18,891
What did you want to talk about?

884
00:39:18,891 --> 00:39:20,926
You haven't even introduced yourself yet.

885
00:39:22,528 --> 00:39:23,696
So...

886
00:39:23,696 --> 00:39:27,066
I thought it might be good to say this
before my introduction.

887
00:39:29,201 --> 00:39:32,705
On the first day
when we made our choices,

888
00:39:33,839 --> 00:39:36,075
that has been weighing on me.

889
00:39:36,075 --> 00:39:37,009
Why?

890
00:39:38,144 --> 00:39:39,612
(Day 1 First-impression choice)

891
00:39:39,612 --> 00:39:40,780
Nice to meet you.

892
00:39:41,914 --> 00:39:45,618
(Ha Yoon chose Dong Young,)

893
00:39:46,552 --> 00:39:51,724
(but Dong Young did not choose Ha Yoon.)

894
00:39:51,957 --> 00:39:53,159
That was the worst.

895
00:39:54,093 --> 00:39:55,528
The worst choice.

896
00:39:57,396 --> 00:40:00,766
To be honest, I'm only saying this now,

897
00:40:00,766 --> 00:40:02,568
but it has been weighing on me
all this time.

898
00:40:02,568 --> 00:40:04,036
Say it on your knees.

899
00:40:04,036 --> 00:40:05,905
I felt uncomfortable the whole time.

900
00:40:05,905 --> 00:40:07,106
My goodness.

901
00:40:07,106 --> 00:40:08,407
It bothered me the whole time.

902
00:40:08,407 --> 00:40:10,976
I wanted to clear it up personally.

903
00:40:11,277 --> 00:40:12,578
Thank you.

904
00:40:14,747 --> 00:40:18,150
I am so curious
about your self-introduction, Dong Young.

905
00:40:18,350 --> 00:40:19,752
Where you live...

906
00:40:21,854 --> 00:40:23,723
and what you do,

907
00:40:23,723 --> 00:40:26,025
and how you've lived your life.

908
00:40:26,025 --> 00:40:28,027
Let's talk more
after your self-introduction.

909
00:40:30,062 --> 00:40:31,764
And after that too,

910
00:40:31,764 --> 00:40:35,334
I hope you become
more curious about me too.

911
00:40:36,369 --> 00:40:37,837
Good.

912
00:40:37,837 --> 00:40:38,871
I also...

913
00:40:43,676 --> 00:40:45,144
For the first time since coming here,

914
00:40:45,845 --> 00:40:46,946
my heart skipped a beat.

915
00:40:49,181 --> 00:40:52,284
(No way)

916
00:40:52,618 --> 00:40:55,287
But you take such good care
of the people around you.

917
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:57,423
Taking care of people is...

918
00:40:57,423 --> 00:40:58,324
Is that just your nature?

919
00:40:58,324 --> 00:40:59,325
I think it is.

920
00:41:00,192 --> 00:41:01,260
I also kind of...

921
00:41:01,260 --> 00:41:05,164
have this trait...

922
00:41:05,164 --> 00:41:08,601
where I feel like
I should make my people happy.

923
00:41:08,601 --> 00:41:09,668
That value.

924
00:41:10,870 --> 00:41:12,338
When did it become part of you?

925
00:41:14,673 --> 00:41:16,675
After I started working.

926
00:41:16,675 --> 00:41:19,845
After I started working,
earning my own money,

927
00:41:19,845 --> 00:41:20,846
and...

928
00:41:21,247 --> 00:41:22,715
buying things for my mom,

929
00:41:23,449 --> 00:41:24,817
and buying things for my younger sibling.

930
00:41:25,418 --> 00:41:29,855
You feel happiness from things like that,

931
00:41:29,855 --> 00:41:35,628
but I wonder if you feel happiness
in everyday life.

932
00:41:36,929 --> 00:41:38,297
How do you feel?

933
00:41:38,297 --> 00:41:41,567
I really don't get stressed when I work.

934
00:41:42,601 --> 00:41:44,570
I'm happy while working.

935
00:41:44,570 --> 00:41:45,538
Wait.

936
00:41:47,907 --> 00:41:49,108
That could be true.

937
00:41:50,109 --> 00:41:52,244
I was worried about that.

938
00:41:53,145 --> 00:41:55,748
Even if you take care of others,

939
00:41:55,748 --> 00:41:57,983
you have to be able
to take care of yourself...

940
00:41:57,983 --> 00:41:59,552
to take care of others.

941
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:03,189
- In any case.
- I think that's true.

942
00:42:03,189 --> 00:42:07,793
So I just wondered
if you were taking care of yourself.

943
00:42:08,094 --> 00:42:09,195
Why is he so charming?

944
00:42:14,266 --> 00:42:21,207
(Ha Yoon chokes up
at Dong Young's question.)

945
00:42:24,276 --> 00:42:26,545
- I'm sorry, I was too...
- No.

946
00:42:26,545 --> 00:42:28,114
- I'm sorry.
- No.

947
00:42:31,917 --> 00:42:33,552
I keep making you cry.

948
00:42:33,552 --> 00:42:34,520
No, that's not it.

949
00:42:40,126 --> 00:42:41,827
I was kind of shocked.

950
00:42:42,762 --> 00:42:46,799
While taking care of people around me
and working,

951
00:42:47,099 --> 00:42:49,168
I think it's true
that I didn't take care of myself.

952
00:42:51,037 --> 00:42:53,239
I think that's why I cried.

953
00:42:54,306 --> 00:42:58,044
I never expected that.

954
00:42:58,778 --> 00:43:01,247
At marriageable age, and at her age,

955
00:43:01,247 --> 00:43:03,616
rather than a fun, lighthearted man,

956
00:43:03,616 --> 00:43:06,519
you want a man who recognizes you
and sees how you have lived.

957
00:43:06,519 --> 00:43:08,721
He makes her look back at herself...

958
00:43:08,721 --> 00:43:10,723
to something she didn't realize herself.

959
00:43:10,723 --> 00:43:13,092
He touched exactly that point.

960
00:43:13,859 --> 00:43:16,362
I think I found happiness elsewhere too,

961
00:43:16,362 --> 00:43:17,863
but when it came to myself,

962
00:43:18,898 --> 00:43:20,633
I kept living with the question,

963
00:43:20,633 --> 00:43:22,568
"Could I find happiness in myself?"

964
00:43:23,102 --> 00:43:24,870
I think it's been that way until now.

965
00:43:24,870 --> 00:43:25,705
So...

966
00:43:25,705 --> 00:43:27,573
Did you find a way?

967
00:43:27,573 --> 00:43:28,607
I came here to find it.

968
00:43:29,508 --> 00:43:30,943
If I can't find it,
let's find it together.

969
00:43:32,445 --> 00:43:33,579
Unbelievable.

970
00:43:33,579 --> 00:43:34,580
That's also a way.

971
00:43:35,915 --> 00:43:37,116
If I cannot figure it out alone...

972
00:43:37,683 --> 00:43:39,585
I hope they work out.

973
00:43:39,585 --> 00:43:40,986
I told you he would make it.

974
00:43:40,986 --> 00:43:43,856
That thought just came to me now.

975
00:43:44,857 --> 00:43:46,726
To enjoy the chicken-and-beer pairing...

976
00:43:46,726 --> 00:43:50,796
(Shin Woo and Da Hye's one-on-one date)

977
00:43:55,935 --> 00:43:59,138
How did you feel
when you heard my introduction?

978
00:43:59,138 --> 00:44:02,942
You were far more amazing than I expected.

979
00:44:02,942 --> 00:44:03,676
Thank you.

980
00:44:03,676 --> 00:44:05,711
I was like,
"Someone like this is in front of me?"

981
00:44:05,711 --> 00:44:06,912
Not at all.

982
00:44:06,912 --> 00:44:08,948
I could only admire you.

983
00:44:09,849 --> 00:44:12,118
I have done a lot of things,
one after another.

984
00:44:12,118 --> 00:44:13,652
- Yes.
- Right.

985
00:44:16,322 --> 00:44:20,426
How was the two-on-one date?

986
00:44:20,426 --> 00:44:22,461
My mother...

987
00:44:22,461 --> 00:44:24,864
I don't think she chose
after hearing about Jeong Yoon.

988
00:44:24,864 --> 00:44:27,233
I think she chose
only after talking to her mother.

989
00:44:27,233 --> 00:44:29,368
So I wondered if this was right.

990
00:44:31,270 --> 00:44:33,172
First of all,

991
00:44:33,172 --> 00:44:36,442
I don't want to burden you, Da Hye.

992
00:44:36,876 --> 00:44:40,012
I feel like I'm keeping you
to myself too much.

993
00:44:40,312 --> 00:44:43,549
- No.
- So I want you to experience others too,

994
00:44:43,549 --> 00:44:45,251
talk with them,

995
00:44:46,519 --> 00:44:48,287
and then see how much better I am.

996
00:44:51,557 --> 00:44:53,826
You're the best.

997
00:44:53,826 --> 00:44:54,894
Seriously.

998
00:44:56,228 --> 00:44:58,330
You're really cool.

999
00:44:59,699 --> 00:45:00,766
In that case,

1000
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:03,402
this question may be...

1001
00:45:03,402 --> 00:45:05,137
a little deep.

1002
00:45:05,771 --> 00:45:06,772
If...

1003
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:10,342
You said you had no religion then,

1004
00:45:10,342 --> 00:45:16,582
so what would you think
if the other person asked,

1005
00:45:16,582 --> 00:45:17,717
"Do you want to go to church together?"

1006
00:45:18,178 --> 00:45:20,380
I feel like Shin Woo will suddenly...

1007
00:45:20,380 --> 00:45:22,015
start going to church tomorrow.

1008
00:45:22,782 --> 00:45:27,187
Because I'm honest and not good at lying,

1009
00:45:27,187 --> 00:45:28,088
I will be truly honest.

1010
00:45:28,088 --> 00:45:29,522
- If I speak really honestly,
- Of course.

1011
00:45:29,522 --> 00:45:30,790
You can say, "I won't go!"

1012
00:45:32,259 --> 00:45:33,593
I would go.

1013
00:45:35,161 --> 00:45:37,097
If you asked me to go, I would go,

1014
00:45:38,298 --> 00:45:42,802
but I'm not sure faith would come to me.

1015
00:45:42,802 --> 00:45:45,972
But as a way of spending time together,

1016
00:45:45,972 --> 00:45:47,807
I think going together would be okay.

1017
00:45:47,807 --> 00:45:51,077
Could you really do that?

1018
00:45:51,077 --> 00:45:53,346
Do they have hourly services at dawn too?

1019
00:45:55,982 --> 00:45:57,617
Do you go, by any chance?

1020
00:45:58,151 --> 00:45:59,953
I don't sleep much in the morning.

1021
00:46:00,387 --> 00:46:02,689
I think it might be nice
to go at dawn and come back.

1022
00:46:03,189 --> 00:46:06,860
(Ready to go starting at dawn tomorrow)

1023
00:46:06,860 --> 00:46:09,195
Even if my mind wanders
while we are at church together,

1024
00:46:09,562 --> 00:46:13,133
I felt like just being next to her
would be nice.

1025
00:46:13,133 --> 00:46:14,367
So I said I could go...

1026
00:46:14,367 --> 00:46:18,138
to show her
that I am consistent and sincere.

1027
00:46:18,939 --> 00:46:24,010
I thought speaking kindly was hard,

1028
00:46:25,812 --> 00:46:27,914
but with you, it seems ingrained in you.

1029
00:46:29,149 --> 00:46:30,116
Da Hye,

1030
00:46:32,052 --> 00:46:33,453
you are my ideal type.

1031
00:46:33,453 --> 00:46:34,654
- Really?
- Yes.

1032
00:46:36,656 --> 00:46:38,024
That made me flutter.

1033
00:46:38,024 --> 00:46:39,993
I couldn't say something like that.

1034
00:46:39,993 --> 00:46:42,028
Not just anyone can say that.

1035
00:46:42,529 --> 00:46:43,463
Da Hye,

1036
00:46:45,332 --> 00:46:46,733
you are my ideal type.

1037
00:46:46,733 --> 00:46:48,435
- Really?
- Yes.

1038
00:46:48,435 --> 00:46:49,603
(A confession
only Shin Woo can make on Day 2)

1039
00:46:49,603 --> 00:46:51,938
That's amazing. Looks too?

1040
00:46:51,938 --> 00:46:52,839
Yes.

1041
00:46:54,774 --> 00:46:57,110
Let's eat this. Eat and get some strength.

1042
00:46:57,844 --> 00:46:59,512
Eat a lot, get your strength up,

1043
00:47:00,313 --> 00:47:01,748
and go on dates too.

1044
00:47:02,616 --> 00:47:04,851
I knew men wouldn't...

1045
00:47:04,851 --> 00:47:05,919
Come to me, right?

1046
00:47:05,919 --> 00:47:07,621
I knew they wouldn't come.

1047
00:47:07,621 --> 00:47:09,789
I expected it too, to some extent.

1048
00:47:09,789 --> 00:47:10,624
Okay.

1049
00:47:10,624 --> 00:47:14,628
Eat chicken and get some strength,

1050
00:47:14,628 --> 00:47:15,729
then try your best.

1051
00:47:16,896 --> 00:47:18,932
I've already let go of expectations...

1052
00:47:18,932 --> 00:47:20,133
thinking I might leave
without finding a match here.

1053
00:47:20,133 --> 00:47:22,936
Don't say that, please.
Don't say it first.

1054
00:47:22,936 --> 00:47:24,404
Do not decide that already.

1055
00:47:24,404 --> 00:47:26,840
Right. Her mother is saying everything.

1056
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:29,175
From what I see,

1057
00:47:29,175 --> 00:47:31,244
Kang Hyeon really did not listen
to her mother growing up.

1058
00:47:31,811 --> 00:47:35,315
Even though her mother understands her
so well and says everything she needs,

1059
00:47:35,315 --> 00:47:37,017
she doesn't listen to her mom.

1060
00:47:38,285 --> 00:47:41,221
I'm going to try now,
but I'm telling you in advance.

1061
00:47:41,221 --> 00:47:42,322
I know.

1062
00:47:42,989 --> 00:47:45,458
I know. Do you think I don't know you?

1063
00:47:46,126 --> 00:47:47,560
This is driving me crazy. I'm so annoyed.

1064
00:47:49,629 --> 00:47:51,831
See, she's not okay.

1065
00:47:51,831 --> 00:47:52,732
Right.

1066
00:47:55,268 --> 00:47:56,937
Mom and Dad...

1067
00:47:56,937 --> 00:47:58,772
I'm not sure about Dad,

1068
00:47:58,772 --> 00:48:01,541
but you, Mom, from when I was little,

1069
00:48:01,541 --> 00:48:02,842
always felt sorry for me.

1070
00:48:03,677 --> 00:48:05,412
Because there were so many things
we couldn't do for you.

1071
00:48:05,412 --> 00:48:06,980
What didn't you and Dad do for me?

1072
00:48:09,316 --> 00:48:10,450
There are many things.

1073
00:48:15,388 --> 00:48:17,824
You and Dad raised me
with everything you had.

1074
00:48:19,759 --> 00:48:24,731
(Kang Hyeon bursts into tears
thinking of her parents.)

1075
00:48:25,265 --> 00:48:26,967
Why are you crying?

1076
00:48:26,967 --> 00:48:28,702
What's wrong?

1077
00:48:30,370 --> 00:48:31,271
Lee Kang Hyeon.

1078
00:48:31,271 --> 00:48:32,372
Yes?

1079
00:48:32,372 --> 00:48:33,773
Get a hold of yourself.

1080
00:48:34,341 --> 00:48:36,776
I love her mother so much.

1081
00:48:36,776 --> 00:48:38,578
Isn't her mother great?

1082
00:48:38,578 --> 00:48:40,547
I love her mother so much.

1083
00:48:40,547 --> 00:48:42,215
This is not the time...

1084
00:48:42,215 --> 00:48:45,352
to talk about how Mom and Dad
raised you long ago.

1085
00:48:45,352 --> 00:48:47,187
This is not the time for that.

1086
00:48:47,187 --> 00:48:48,455
You need to get a hold of yourself.

1087
00:48:48,455 --> 00:48:52,425
You should think, "Let's try again."

1088
00:48:52,425 --> 00:48:53,860
Get a hold of yourself.

1089
00:48:54,628 --> 00:48:55,929
It's because I'm emotional.

1090
00:48:55,929 --> 00:48:57,264
Get a hold of yourself.

1091
00:48:58,098 --> 00:48:59,466
So...

1092
00:48:59,466 --> 00:49:00,367
It's okay.

1093
00:49:01,768 --> 00:49:03,136
What's happened to me here...

1094
00:49:03,737 --> 00:49:06,673
I know it makes you feel sorry for me,
so it hurts.

1095
00:49:08,008 --> 00:49:09,142
I do feel sorry for you, but...

1096
00:49:09,142 --> 00:49:11,311
Right? That feeling.

1097
00:49:11,311 --> 00:49:12,145
I do feel sorry for you,

1098
00:49:12,145 --> 00:49:15,348
but it's not like my heart is breaking.

1099
00:49:15,348 --> 00:49:16,917
Coming here and...

1100
00:49:16,917 --> 00:49:19,185
- She is the best.
- She's amazing.

1101
00:49:19,185 --> 00:49:20,887
Seriously.

1102
00:49:21,187 --> 00:49:23,456
If you don't like someone,
you don't have to do anything.

1103
00:49:23,456 --> 00:49:25,759
If you do like someone, you can.

1104
00:49:25,759 --> 00:49:28,862
Why are you crying
like it's the end of the world? Enough.

1105
00:49:28,862 --> 00:49:30,397
When did I cry
like it was the end of the world, Mom?

1106
00:49:30,397 --> 00:49:32,165
- Don't cry.
- It's not that serious.

1107
00:49:32,165 --> 00:49:34,334
People will think
I'm crying because no man chose me,

1108
00:49:34,334 --> 00:49:36,136
and that I'm crying
like it's the end of the world.

1109
00:49:36,136 --> 00:49:38,705
That's basically why you're crying now.

1110
00:49:38,705 --> 00:49:39,673
Don't cry.

1111
00:49:39,673 --> 00:49:41,675
She is so accurate.

1112
00:49:42,542 --> 00:49:44,711
She says everything I wanted to say.

1113
00:49:45,078 --> 00:49:46,947
She says she's crying
because I might be having a hard time,

1114
00:49:46,947 --> 00:49:49,182
but honestly,
I'm not having that hard a time.

1115
00:49:49,182 --> 00:49:51,685
I wondered,
"Is she using me as an excuse to cry?"

1116
00:49:51,685 --> 00:49:53,620
I was like, "Stop crying."

1117
00:49:53,620 --> 00:49:56,523
I'm sure she's worried about me,

1118
00:49:56,523 --> 00:49:57,824
but also,

1119
00:49:57,824 --> 00:50:00,760
I think she was crying
because of her pride.

1120
00:50:00,760 --> 00:50:01,928
That's how it looked to me.

1121
00:50:03,897 --> 00:50:05,498
(Double thumbs-up
for her mother's insight)

1122
00:50:05,498 --> 00:50:07,167
- A mom is a mom.
- A fact bomb.

1123
00:50:07,167 --> 00:50:08,635
She's amazing.

1124
00:50:09,336 --> 00:50:12,739
Her mother said...

1125
00:50:12,739 --> 00:50:14,941
exactly what I wanted to say.

1126
00:50:15,575 --> 00:50:19,079
The best and the funniest part was...

1127
00:50:19,079 --> 00:50:24,184
Lee Kang Hyeon
and her mother's chicken-and-beer date.

1128
00:50:24,184 --> 00:50:27,053
- It was the best.
- I think it was the best.

1129
00:50:28,121 --> 00:50:29,489
Did you enjoy your meal?

1130
00:50:29,489 --> 00:50:30,991
(After the date,
Shin Woo walks Da Hye all the way inside.)

1131
00:50:30,991 --> 00:50:32,225
Thank you for choosing her.

1132
00:50:33,293 --> 00:50:35,629
Thank you for giving birth
to such a beautiful daughter.

1133
00:50:35,629 --> 00:50:36,596
What?

1134
00:50:37,764 --> 00:50:38,865
This is insane.

1135
00:50:39,766 --> 00:50:42,602
This is insane. He actually said that?

1136
00:50:44,471 --> 00:50:46,039
I thought they were already dating.

1137
00:50:46,039 --> 00:50:48,475
Did they set the wedding date already?

1138
00:50:48,475 --> 00:50:52,312
Even if Da Hye's mother
did not like Shin Woo much at first,

1139
00:50:52,312 --> 00:50:54,047
her interest in him must have shot up.

1140
00:50:54,047 --> 00:50:55,982
But Shin Woo's skill is...

1141
00:50:55,982 --> 00:50:58,919
that he says things like that
without sounding cheesy.

1142
00:50:58,919 --> 00:51:00,754
- He says it so kindly.
- So warmly.

1143
00:51:01,054 --> 00:51:02,889
Tomorrow is the day you get chosen.

1144
00:51:02,889 --> 00:51:03,723
Right.

1145
00:51:03,723 --> 00:51:05,825
(Pick me.)

1146
00:51:05,825 --> 00:51:06,726
Please remember me.

1147
00:51:06,726 --> 00:51:08,361
What does this man do?

1148
00:51:09,162 --> 00:51:10,563
I'm so curious about him.

1149
00:51:10,563 --> 00:51:12,499
- Have a good night.
- Thank you.

1150
00:51:14,134 --> 00:51:16,703
Now that I see him, he is so earnest.

1151
00:51:16,703 --> 00:51:20,106
I really can't put
today's conversation into words.

1152
00:51:20,473 --> 00:51:21,875
Seriously.

1153
00:51:21,875 --> 00:51:23,777
Should they go straight
to the wedding hall?

1154
00:51:23,777 --> 00:51:25,512
- He's going straight.
- Yes.

1155
00:51:25,512 --> 00:51:28,615
And honestly,
even with Do Yoon's mother here,

1156
00:51:28,615 --> 00:51:31,685
I honestly don't think
coming all the way in is easy.

1157
00:51:31,685 --> 00:51:33,720
Even after coming in,

1158
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:35,322
his gaze went only to Da Hye's mother.

1159
00:51:35,322 --> 00:51:37,357
He only gave me a quick eye greeting.

1160
00:51:37,357 --> 00:51:39,225
Now, you just have to decide.

1161
00:51:40,226 --> 00:51:41,661
Are you going to marry her off quickly?

1162
00:51:42,662 --> 00:51:45,665
I would welcome him with open arms.

1163
00:51:48,835 --> 00:51:50,103
(Do Yoon returns from her date too.)

1164
00:51:50,103 --> 00:51:51,838
- Welcome back.
- You're back.

1165
00:51:52,339 --> 00:51:54,975
Things are chaotic with Da Hye now.

1166
00:51:54,975 --> 00:51:56,376
He's going completely straight for her.

1167
00:51:56,376 --> 00:51:57,844
Did you basically get a confession?

1168
00:51:59,579 --> 00:52:00,547
Right, that's what it was.

1169
00:52:00,547 --> 00:52:01,414
Really?

1170
00:52:01,414 --> 00:52:03,750
Ye Chan didn't walk you back?

1171
00:52:03,750 --> 00:52:05,352
He came to the front.

1172
00:52:05,352 --> 00:52:06,319
He didn't come inside.

1173
00:52:06,319 --> 00:52:07,654
He didn't come in.

1174
00:52:07,654 --> 00:52:09,689
That is why Shin Woo is amazing.

1175
00:52:09,689 --> 00:52:11,124
He came in.

1176
00:52:11,358 --> 00:52:12,492
I guess he's made up his mind.

1177
00:52:12,492 --> 00:52:13,893
Exactly. How was it?

1178
00:52:13,893 --> 00:52:14,961
Me?

1179
00:52:14,961 --> 00:52:17,264
- The conversation flowed really well.
- Really?

1180
00:52:17,564 --> 00:52:19,032
You must be tired. Go in.

1181
00:52:19,032 --> 00:52:19,966
Should we rest a bit?

1182
00:52:19,966 --> 00:52:21,635
We talked so much.

1183
00:52:21,635 --> 00:52:23,770
- I'll go rest.
- I'll go inside.

1184
00:52:23,770 --> 00:52:24,838
Let's go too.

1185
00:52:24,838 --> 00:52:28,141
(Da Hye and her mother enter their room.)

1186
00:52:28,942 --> 00:52:31,578
I'm curious what our Shin Woo said.

1187
00:52:31,578 --> 00:52:33,847
- "Our Shin Woo?"
- He's really good with words.

1188
00:52:33,847 --> 00:52:35,582
And to be completely honest,

1189
00:52:35,582 --> 00:52:37,284
he's an incredibly direct man.

1190
00:52:37,517 --> 00:52:40,754
I felt certain
this man would really come all the way.

1191
00:52:41,755 --> 00:52:44,424
The person
I'm most interested in right now...

1192
00:52:45,358 --> 00:52:46,726
is Shin Woo.

1193
00:52:47,327 --> 00:52:50,297
But since it's still Day Two,

1194
00:52:50,297 --> 00:52:52,132
I think I have a lot on my mind.

1195
00:52:52,532 --> 00:52:53,934
Still, to have no regrets,

1196
00:52:53,934 --> 00:52:57,137
I plan to talk with other people too.

1197
00:52:57,537 --> 00:53:00,974
She's wondering
if she's deciding too quickly.

1198
00:53:00,974 --> 00:53:01,875
Right.

1199
00:53:01,875 --> 00:53:03,677
Because it's still Day Two.

1200
00:53:03,677 --> 00:53:07,013
I think she has some regrets or worries.

1201
00:53:08,982 --> 00:53:11,618
- Mother, I'm back.
- Yes.

1202
00:53:11,618 --> 00:53:13,720
- How was it?
- Pardon?

1203
00:53:14,154 --> 00:53:15,689
- It was so nice.
- Really?

1204
00:53:15,689 --> 00:53:18,458
Look at his face.

1205
00:53:18,458 --> 00:53:19,793
He really likes her.

1206
00:53:19,793 --> 00:53:22,295
Da Hye really does have such a cute look.

1207
00:53:22,295 --> 00:53:23,797
And she's pretty.

1208
00:53:23,797 --> 00:53:25,265
- And she keeps smiling.
- Yes.

1209
00:53:25,865 --> 00:53:27,500
But still, get to know others too.

1210
00:53:27,500 --> 00:53:28,935
I should get to know them.

1211
00:53:29,169 --> 00:53:30,870
Even after today's date,

1212
00:53:30,870 --> 00:53:33,540
she said his smile went
all the way up here.

1213
00:53:33,540 --> 00:53:35,675
I didn't know he had that side.

1214
00:53:35,675 --> 00:53:38,011
That he would be such a direct man.

1215
00:53:38,411 --> 00:53:40,380
His mother still doesn't like it.

1216
00:53:40,981 --> 00:53:42,882
As a one-on-one date,

1217
00:53:43,183 --> 00:53:46,386
talk with several people.

1218
00:53:46,386 --> 00:53:48,321
Going straight for someone is a no.

1219
00:53:48,321 --> 00:53:50,957
Don't go straight for someone.
That's ridiculous.

1220
00:53:52,225 --> 00:53:55,095
Is there someone
who's your favorite, Ms. Kim?

1221
00:53:55,095 --> 00:53:56,029
Me?

1222
00:53:57,230 --> 00:53:58,365
Why are you asking me a leading question?

1223
00:53:58,365 --> 00:54:00,267
I'm someone who easily
falls for those questions.

1224
00:54:00,267 --> 00:54:02,335
So easily.

1225
00:54:03,370 --> 00:54:04,938
I was just so curious.

1226
00:54:04,938 --> 00:54:06,906
Ye Chan is so tall,

1227
00:54:06,906 --> 00:54:09,242
so in case he becomes a rival...

1228
00:54:09,242 --> 00:54:11,077
In case he becomes competition?

1229
00:54:11,077 --> 00:54:12,646
I need to keep him in check...

1230
00:54:12,646 --> 00:54:14,414
and block him from climbing up.

1231
00:54:16,783 --> 00:54:17,851
(The target in question appears
right on cue.)

1232
00:54:17,851 --> 00:54:19,653
The target in question appears
right on cue.

1233
00:54:21,421 --> 00:54:22,722
Knock, knock.

1234
00:54:22,722 --> 00:54:23,990
Hello.

1235
00:54:23,990 --> 00:54:25,025
Ye Chan.

1236
00:54:25,025 --> 00:54:26,126
How was it, Ye Chan?

1237
00:54:26,126 --> 00:54:27,227
It went well.

1238
00:54:27,427 --> 00:54:29,296
Did your interest go up?

1239
00:54:29,296 --> 00:54:30,931
- I think it went up a little more.
- Really?

1240
00:54:32,032 --> 00:54:34,200
About Do Yoon?

1241
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:35,535
He said it was so nice.

1242
00:54:36,202 --> 00:54:38,905
I mean, he's smiling so much now.

1243
00:54:38,905 --> 00:54:41,141
His mouth is about to split.

1244
00:54:41,141 --> 00:54:42,309
It will split soon.

1245
00:54:42,309 --> 00:54:44,678
Korea's best program, Match to Marry.

1246
00:54:46,179 --> 00:54:47,147
Seriously.

1247
00:54:47,147 --> 00:54:49,249
I'll say bye now and see you again later.

1248
00:54:49,249 --> 00:54:50,350
See you later.

1249
00:54:50,350 --> 00:54:53,453
(They rush goodbye
before Shin Woo's mouth splits more.)

1250
00:54:54,521 --> 00:54:56,356
- Chan.
- Yeah?

1251
00:54:56,356 --> 00:54:57,357
How was it?

1252
00:54:58,258 --> 00:54:59,626
Do Yoon was...

1253
00:55:01,628 --> 00:55:02,996
Was she what you expected?

1254
00:55:03,396 --> 00:55:04,598
Yes, the conversation...

1255
00:55:05,298 --> 00:55:07,200
made me think
it would be nice to talk more.

1256
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:09,135
The person I want to get to know more...

1257
00:55:09,135 --> 00:55:10,303
is Do Yoon...

1258
00:55:11,271 --> 00:55:13,540
and Da Hye.
I still haven't talked to Da Hye.

1259
00:55:14,040 --> 00:55:17,344
Da Hye has already
been claimed over there.

1260
00:55:18,712 --> 00:55:20,480
That doesn't matter.

1261
00:55:21,448 --> 00:55:24,618
You're going to compete with Shin Woo too.

1262
00:55:24,618 --> 00:55:27,320
I don't really think of it as competition.
I'll just do my own thing.

1263
00:55:27,320 --> 00:55:28,355
Right.

1264
00:55:28,355 --> 00:55:29,856
That's confidence.

1265
00:55:29,856 --> 00:55:31,591
The confidence of a popular man.

1266
00:55:32,492 --> 00:55:36,763
First place is Jeong Yoon.

1267
00:55:36,763 --> 00:55:38,365
For now, it's still Jeong Yoon.

1268
00:55:38,365 --> 00:55:41,167
Second place is still Da Hye.

1269
00:55:41,167 --> 00:55:42,902
Third place is Do Yoon.

1270
00:55:43,370 --> 00:55:47,274
Because I have not really talked
with Da Hye yet,

1271
00:55:47,274 --> 00:55:51,144
and I only had my conversation
with Do Yoon.

1272
00:55:51,611 --> 00:55:54,314
To be honest,
I didn't feel a romantic spark.

1273
00:55:55,382 --> 00:55:57,284
I plan to talk with Da Hye one-on-one,

1274
00:55:57,284 --> 00:55:59,219
even if briefly.

1275
00:55:59,986 --> 00:56:01,955
He's very thorough.

1276
00:56:01,955 --> 00:56:03,123
Exactly.

1277
00:56:03,123 --> 00:56:05,625
I'm suddenly having a strange thought.

1278
00:56:05,625 --> 00:56:07,127
At that rate,
he could end up with nothing.

1279
00:56:07,127 --> 00:56:08,395
That can happen.

1280
00:56:09,496 --> 00:56:13,900
(Ye Chan immediately comes outside.)

1281
00:56:18,138 --> 00:56:19,072
Da Hye?

1282
00:56:19,606 --> 00:56:21,408
- Hello.
- Hello.

1283
00:56:21,408 --> 00:56:23,643
Where are you going? Are you going in now?

1284
00:56:25,412 --> 00:56:26,646
Thanks to your voice,

1285
00:56:26,646 --> 00:56:29,683
you're one of the people
whose job I'm most curious about.

1286
00:56:30,584 --> 00:56:32,752
There have been a few theories.

1287
00:56:32,752 --> 00:56:33,653
A voice actor theory.

1288
00:56:33,653 --> 00:56:35,522
A new theory came out today too.

1289
00:56:35,522 --> 00:56:36,856
- What is it?
- Doctor theory.

1290
00:56:37,991 --> 00:56:39,759
That's the first time
I've ever heard that in my life.

1291
00:56:41,061 --> 00:56:42,462
So it's probably not that.

1292
00:56:43,697 --> 00:56:44,564
Who knows?

1293
00:56:47,100 --> 00:56:48,201
(Ye Chan and Da Hye enter the book café.)

1294
00:56:48,201 --> 00:56:50,103
- This is nice.
- This place is really nice.

1295
00:56:50,670 --> 00:56:54,074
I was surprised you called me first.

1296
00:56:54,074 --> 00:56:55,976
I was like, "No one would call me."

1297
00:56:56,209 --> 00:56:58,244
The timing was perfect
when we ran into each other.

1298
00:56:58,244 --> 00:56:59,245
I know.

1299
00:57:00,513 --> 00:57:03,516
Actually, since we suddenly
ran into each other...

1300
00:57:03,516 --> 00:57:05,885
If it had been a one-on-one date,
I would have gone home...

1301
00:57:05,885 --> 00:57:09,189
and looked over the study notes
I worked hard to organize.

1302
00:57:09,189 --> 00:57:11,491
Like right before an exam...

1303
00:57:11,491 --> 00:57:12,726
Such a model student.

1304
00:57:12,726 --> 00:57:16,129
I should've skimmed them quickly,
but I couldn't.

1305
00:57:16,129 --> 00:57:16,997
Right.

1306
00:57:16,997 --> 00:57:18,732
You were born in 1994.

1307
00:57:18,732 --> 00:57:20,066
That's right.

1308
00:57:20,066 --> 00:57:22,535
- And you work in Pilates.
- That's right.

1309
00:57:22,535 --> 00:57:25,739
That's right.
You remember it all. That was everything.

1310
00:57:26,673 --> 00:57:28,008
I wrote down a lot, though.

1311
00:57:28,842 --> 00:57:30,510
I was so curious about what Ye Chan means.

1312
00:57:30,510 --> 00:57:33,513
I wondered if it meant what we thought.

1313
00:57:34,147 --> 00:57:36,316
- That's right.
- I see.

1314
00:57:36,316 --> 00:57:38,685
Then do you share
the same religion as your mother?

1315
00:57:39,219 --> 00:57:41,821
Yes, the same religion.

1316
00:57:42,355 --> 00:57:46,092
Do you consider yourself quite devout?

1317
00:57:46,860 --> 00:57:48,895
I'm not very devout.

1318
00:57:48,895 --> 00:57:51,131
- It would be odd to say no.
- You're honest.

1319
00:57:51,631 --> 00:57:53,633
(Squinty smile)

1320
00:57:56,903 --> 00:57:59,706
I'm sorry to interrupt,

1321
00:57:59,706 --> 00:58:02,542
but your eyes are alive.

1322
00:58:03,143 --> 00:58:05,812
It's because I have good stamina.
Are you tired?

1323
00:58:06,212 --> 00:58:10,283
I keep having an occupational habit,

1324
00:58:10,283 --> 00:58:11,651
and I keep looking at your feet.

1325
00:58:12,185 --> 00:58:14,421
Those feet are such sad feet.

1326
00:58:14,421 --> 00:58:16,089
You're also slightly flat-footed.

1327
00:58:16,623 --> 00:58:18,224
That's the first time
I've ever heard that phrase,

1328
00:58:18,224 --> 00:58:19,459
"sad feet."

1329
00:58:21,328 --> 00:58:22,762
I'm not completely flat-footed.

1330
00:58:22,762 --> 00:58:24,230
You're right.

1331
00:58:24,230 --> 00:58:25,699
Come here for a second.

1332
00:58:27,734 --> 00:58:28,902
(Press)

1333
00:58:28,902 --> 00:58:30,203
No!

1334
00:58:30,203 --> 00:58:31,871
It hurts a lot, right?

1335
00:58:31,871 --> 00:58:33,106
His projection is very good.

1336
00:58:33,106 --> 00:58:34,474
And this...

1337
00:58:34,474 --> 00:58:36,910
When you press here, it hurts a lot.

1338
00:58:37,911 --> 00:58:38,812
It is no joke, right?

1339
00:58:39,379 --> 00:58:40,680
Lastly, here.

1340
00:58:40,680 --> 00:58:42,449
- He must really be in pain.
- It must hurt so much.

1341
00:58:42,449 --> 00:58:44,050
No.

1342
00:58:44,050 --> 00:58:45,585
My goodness.

1343
00:58:45,585 --> 00:58:47,254
What is that?

1344
00:58:48,922 --> 00:58:50,023
But...

1345
00:58:50,023 --> 00:58:51,858
while talking for the first time,

1346
00:58:51,858 --> 00:58:54,561
having that kind of physical contact...

1347
00:58:54,561 --> 00:58:55,495
is not easy.

1348
00:58:55,495 --> 00:58:56,830
It could be an occupational habit,

1349
00:58:56,830 --> 00:59:00,000
and somehow, her expression
seemed slightly more...

1350
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:03,136
like she was acting cute.

1351
00:59:03,136 --> 00:59:04,571
She had a soft, feminine vibe.

1352
00:59:04,571 --> 00:59:07,340
- And religion.
- Their religion is the same too.

1353
00:59:07,340 --> 00:59:09,676
I'm a little worried about Shin Woo.

1354
00:59:12,379 --> 00:59:15,081
Do you know that feeling
like the world has changed?

1355
00:59:16,283 --> 00:59:18,919
Everything is actually the same,
but the world feels different.

1356
00:59:19,986 --> 00:59:21,121
You're really an F, aren't you?

1357
00:59:21,121 --> 00:59:23,189
I told you I'm a T.

1358
00:59:23,189 --> 00:59:24,791
You seem more F than me.

1359
00:59:24,791 --> 00:59:25,959
I'm definitely a T.

1360
00:59:27,694 --> 00:59:29,162
- See you again tomorrow.
- Yes.

1361
00:59:29,763 --> 00:59:31,331
- Go in.
- Have a nice rest.

1362
00:59:32,632 --> 00:59:35,335
What do I do?
I cried in front of the camera.

1363
00:59:37,570 --> 00:59:40,073
I can't believe this. He made me cry.

1364
00:59:40,573 --> 00:59:42,709
But he didn't know...

1365
00:59:42,709 --> 00:59:43,643
He knew why.

1366
00:59:43,643 --> 00:59:45,145
Really?

1367
00:59:45,145 --> 00:59:46,513
He wasn't flustered at all.

1368
00:59:47,347 --> 00:59:49,249
I thought he was younger,

1369
00:59:49,249 --> 00:59:50,483
but he's definitely not younger.

1370
00:59:50,483 --> 00:59:51,551
He's not younger?

1371
00:59:51,551 --> 00:59:52,586
Really?

1372
00:59:52,586 --> 00:59:55,989
Or he's someone who thinks very deeply.

1373
00:59:55,989 --> 00:59:58,358
His mental age seems
higher than mine, at least.

1374
00:59:59,593 --> 01:00:02,729
That's a relief.
It's not easy for you to feel that.

1375
01:00:02,729 --> 01:00:03,563
Exactly.

1376
01:00:04,364 --> 01:00:06,132
But he's really direct.

1377
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:07,634
Is he?

1378
01:00:07,634 --> 01:00:08,835
He doesn't speak indirectly?

1379
01:00:08,835 --> 01:00:10,236
He doesn't.

1380
01:00:10,236 --> 01:00:13,173
Right. When I said,

1381
01:00:13,173 --> 01:00:16,309
"I guess I don't really know
how to make myself happy,"

1382
01:00:16,309 --> 01:00:18,144
he said, "Then let's find it together."

1383
01:00:19,446 --> 01:00:23,250
He said he was not trying to pressure me,
but we could find a way together.

1384
01:00:23,250 --> 01:00:25,252
(Dong Young's direct lines
make Ha Yoon smile.)

1385
01:00:25,452 --> 01:00:28,255
Each word must have stayed with her.

1386
01:00:28,255 --> 01:00:29,256
I guess so.

1387
01:00:29,789 --> 01:00:31,258
How was it after talking?

1388
01:00:33,226 --> 01:00:34,628
The more I get to know her,

1389
01:00:34,628 --> 01:00:35,595
the more curious I get.

1390
01:00:36,763 --> 01:00:39,666
I wonder what kind of life she's lived.

1391
01:00:41,301 --> 01:00:42,269
I'm curious.

1392
01:00:42,802 --> 01:00:43,970
I'm a T, Mom.

1393
01:00:43,970 --> 01:00:46,573
- What?
- I'm a T in MBTI.

1394
01:00:47,707 --> 01:00:49,743
But in front of her, I become an F.

1395
01:00:50,677 --> 01:00:51,745
Isn't that strange?

1396
01:00:53,079 --> 01:00:54,281
It's strange, right?

1397
01:00:54,281 --> 01:00:55,782
(As if he's Dong Young)

1398
01:00:56,349 --> 01:00:59,085
This side feels all blocked up.

1399
01:01:01,054 --> 01:01:02,923
Would the other men all be similar?

1400
01:01:05,191 --> 01:01:06,126
Where's your room?

1401
01:01:06,126 --> 01:01:07,193
Here.

1402
01:01:08,028 --> 01:01:09,429
The location is pretty good.

1403
01:01:09,429 --> 01:01:11,197
(Jeong Yoon, Seong Mo,
and In Kwon return after the 2-on-1 date.)

1404
01:01:11,576 --> 01:01:13,679
If you're not too tired,

1405
01:01:13,679 --> 01:01:15,380
could we talk one-on-one
for just five minutes?

1406
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:17,049
Yes, sure.

1407
01:01:17,601 --> 01:01:20,037
Seong Mo asked for a one-on-one talk.

1408
01:01:20,044 --> 01:01:21,779
He found the courage.

1409
01:01:22,479 --> 01:01:26,350
When you first entered,

1410
01:01:27,351 --> 01:01:28,752
you immediately caught my eye.

1411
01:01:28,752 --> 01:01:29,987
- Really?
- Yes.

1412
01:01:29,987 --> 01:01:31,589
I really had no idea at all.

1413
01:01:31,589 --> 01:01:34,391
You couldn't have known.
I couldn't look at you properly either.

1414
01:01:35,392 --> 01:01:36,626
Then...

1415
01:01:37,661 --> 01:01:39,362
you received the jeogori, right?

1416
01:01:39,362 --> 01:01:40,730
Yes.

1417
01:01:41,031 --> 01:01:42,566
Isn't it a norigae?

1418
01:01:43,133 --> 01:01:45,435
Jeogori is...

1419
01:01:45,435 --> 01:01:47,237
For a moment, I almost believed it.

1420
01:01:48,205 --> 01:01:49,739
You received the jeogori, right?

1421
01:01:49,739 --> 01:01:51,208
Yes.

1422
01:01:51,208 --> 01:01:52,876
I kept leaving mine in your box.

1423
01:01:52,876 --> 01:01:54,277
Really?

1424
01:01:54,277 --> 01:01:56,012
- I didn't know.
- You received a lot, didn't you?

1425
01:01:56,012 --> 01:01:59,916
No, not that much. Just a modest amount.

1426
01:02:01,017 --> 01:02:03,720
I've never approached a woman first.

1427
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:06,456
Am I the first?

1428
01:02:06,456 --> 01:02:07,524
That's nice.

1429
01:02:08,091 --> 01:02:10,393
I came here wanting to try it,

1430
01:02:10,393 --> 01:02:12,729
to change myself.

1431
01:02:12,729 --> 01:02:14,498
I wanted to step out and gather courage,

1432
01:02:15,165 --> 01:02:16,666
but I thought
the other person might dislike it,

1433
01:02:16,666 --> 01:02:19,035
and I didn't have the courage either,

1434
01:02:19,035 --> 01:02:21,972
so I thought,
"Let's stick to my pattern and be shy."

1435
01:02:21,972 --> 01:02:23,373
I see.

1436
01:02:23,373 --> 01:02:25,175
So you were shy.

1437
01:02:25,175 --> 01:02:27,277
I thought you were cold.

1438
01:02:27,777 --> 01:02:30,447
People say that a lot...

1439
01:02:30,447 --> 01:02:31,948
when they first see my face.

1440
01:02:32,516 --> 01:02:36,086
If you hadn't told me,
I really wouldn't have known at all.

1441
01:02:36,086 --> 01:02:37,988
I really had no idea.

1442
01:02:37,988 --> 01:02:40,557
You talked so much with Kang Hyeon,

1443
01:02:40,557 --> 01:02:42,259
and you were with her
while washing dishes,

1444
01:02:42,259 --> 01:02:44,694
and I heard you even visited
her room separately.

1445
01:02:44,694 --> 01:02:47,998
We're in the same room,
so after I heard that,

1446
01:02:47,998 --> 01:02:49,666
since I'm kind of a pacifist,

1447
01:02:49,666 --> 01:02:52,502
I thought, "Then I should talk
to everyone except for Seong Mo."

1448
01:02:52,502 --> 01:02:53,737
I see.

1449
01:02:53,737 --> 01:02:56,139
Because of that, I didn't talk to you.

1450
01:02:56,139 --> 01:02:58,475
But I wanted to talk with you
at least once.

1451
01:02:58,475 --> 01:02:59,976
Because we hadn't talked at all.

1452
01:03:00,510 --> 01:03:01,478
This is embarrassing.

1453
01:03:02,245 --> 01:03:03,947
From the beginning until now,

1454
01:03:03,947 --> 01:03:07,150
I told Jeong Yoon...

1455
01:03:07,150 --> 01:03:08,652
how I chose and what I felt.

1456
01:03:09,186 --> 01:03:14,357
Even during the two-on-one date,
Jeong Yoon's expression...

1457
01:03:14,357 --> 01:03:17,627
was not that favorable toward me.

1458
01:03:17,627 --> 01:03:20,330
After I told her that,

1459
01:03:20,330 --> 01:03:22,098
her eyes seemed to become
a bit more favorable.

1460
01:03:22,799 --> 01:03:27,170
The person I liked
looked at me differently...

1461
01:03:27,170 --> 01:03:30,841
and treated me better. That felt good.

1462
01:03:31,975 --> 01:03:33,243
This is actually better now.

1463
01:03:33,243 --> 01:03:36,546
Right. You have to talk
to know each other's hearts.

1464
01:03:37,314 --> 01:03:40,984
Jeong Yoon feels nice.

1465
01:03:40,984 --> 01:03:45,388
She seems shy and sincere in a way.

1466
01:03:46,756 --> 01:03:47,958
Not over-the-top.

1467
01:03:48,892 --> 01:03:52,062
You look happier now.

1468
01:03:52,062 --> 01:03:53,663
- Who, me?
- You.

1469
01:03:53,663 --> 01:03:55,432
I mean, earlier,

1470
01:03:55,432 --> 01:03:57,667
when you came back,
you just said you were tired,

1471
01:03:57,667 --> 01:04:00,570
- and didn't say much.
- You're right.

1472
01:04:00,570 --> 01:04:02,772
But now, from the moment you came in,
your eyes are bright.

1473
01:04:02,772 --> 01:04:04,541
We talked just out front.

1474
01:04:04,541 --> 01:04:06,176
Your eyes are sparkling.

1475
01:04:06,977 --> 01:04:09,613
Mom, Seong Mo said
he liked me from the start.

1476
01:04:09,613 --> 01:04:10,380
But?

1477
01:04:10,380 --> 01:04:14,117
He liked me from the first impression,
but we couldn't talk.

1478
01:04:14,117 --> 01:04:17,487
So he really wanted to clear up
the misunderstanding.

1479
01:04:17,487 --> 01:04:19,356
He was too shy to look at me.

1480
01:04:19,356 --> 01:04:21,124
He says he's really shy.

1481
01:04:21,124 --> 01:04:22,959
So he must be totally sincere.

1482
01:04:22,959 --> 01:04:26,596
He wanted to make his appeal
before tomorrow.

1483
01:04:26,596 --> 01:04:29,299
First, I felt very sorry
that I misunderstood him.

1484
01:04:29,299 --> 01:04:31,535
Because he expressed himself clearly,

1485
01:04:31,535 --> 01:04:33,870
I thought I should talk with him more.

1486
01:04:33,870 --> 01:04:36,039
I think she thought he was very cold...

1487
01:04:36,039 --> 01:04:38,108
And not interested in her.

1488
01:04:38,108 --> 01:04:39,476
She thought he had no interest,

1489
01:04:39,476 --> 01:04:40,944
but after talking,

1490
01:04:40,944 --> 01:04:44,514
she feels this unexpected turn,
like he's endlessly kind.

1491
01:04:44,514 --> 01:04:48,151
When cold people suddenly act sweet,

1492
01:04:48,151 --> 01:04:49,119
their appeal rises sharply.

1493
01:04:49,119 --> 01:04:51,454
Falling for that is...

1494
01:04:51,454 --> 01:04:55,125
the plot of many dramas.

1495
01:04:55,692 --> 01:04:58,328
The people I am most interested in,
tied for first,

1496
01:04:58,328 --> 01:05:01,665
are Seong Mo and In Kwon.

1497
01:05:02,285 --> 01:05:05,688
Honestly, I haven't talked much
with In Kwon,

1498
01:05:05,688 --> 01:05:07,991
so I want to ask him too.
What exactly is his ideal type?

1499
01:05:07,991 --> 01:05:10,159
Does he really only like Gong Seung Yeon?

1500
01:05:10,159 --> 01:05:12,528
What else does he look at besides looks?

1501
01:05:12,528 --> 01:05:15,231
And what about me
made a good first impression?

1502
01:05:15,231 --> 01:05:17,000
I want to ask more clearly...

1503
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:19,636
and ask all kinds of things.

1504
01:05:20,207 --> 01:05:21,442
After I touch up my makeup,

1505
01:05:21,442 --> 01:05:24,011
should I go talk with In Kwon?

1506
01:05:24,511 --> 01:05:25,479
You should.

1507
01:05:25,479 --> 01:05:27,981
He said there were things he couldn't ask.

1508
01:05:29,783 --> 01:05:30,818
Where are you going?

1509
01:05:30,818 --> 01:05:31,852
Me?

1510
01:05:31,852 --> 01:05:33,487
Isn't it better to talk at least once?

1511
01:05:34,188 --> 01:05:35,656
I suppose so.

1512
01:05:35,656 --> 01:05:37,691
They say you have to keep moving.

1513
01:05:37,691 --> 01:05:38,759
I think that's true.

1514
01:05:39,660 --> 01:05:41,528
In Kwon.

1515
01:05:42,496 --> 01:05:45,866
(Jeong Yoon heads to In Kwon.)

1516
01:05:45,866 --> 01:05:46,967
- See you.
- Yes.

1517
01:05:48,035 --> 01:05:50,571
- They must be going to each other.
- They'll meet each other.

1518
01:05:50,971 --> 01:05:53,173
This makes it more moving.

1519
01:05:53,173 --> 01:05:55,042
Their telepathy really worked.

1520
01:05:56,910 --> 01:05:59,613
(Jeong Yoon comes to In Kwon's room.)

1521
01:05:59,613 --> 01:06:00,380
(Knock, knock)

1522
01:06:00,380 --> 01:06:01,248
Yes?

1523
01:06:02,549 --> 01:06:04,418
Is In Kwon here?

1524
01:06:04,418 --> 01:06:05,285
He left.

1525
01:06:05,285 --> 01:06:06,253
- He left?
- Yes.

1526
01:06:06,253 --> 01:06:07,254
Okay.

1527
01:06:08,489 --> 01:06:10,357
If he left, it won't work out.

1528
01:06:11,358 --> 01:06:14,828
(Where is In Kwon?)

1529
01:06:16,296 --> 01:06:17,197
Excuse me.

1530
01:06:17,197 --> 01:06:18,198
Yes?

1531
01:06:18,198 --> 01:06:19,266
Do Yoon.

1532
01:06:20,334 --> 01:06:22,002
Who is it?

1533
01:06:22,002 --> 01:06:22,870
Do you want to talk for a moment?

1534
01:06:22,870 --> 01:06:24,304
- Is that okay?
- Yes, one second.

1535
01:06:25,139 --> 01:06:26,406
He went there?

1536
01:06:26,406 --> 01:06:27,441
Do Yoon?

1537
01:06:27,875 --> 01:06:30,377
Right now, my interest in Jeong Yoon...

1538
01:06:30,377 --> 01:06:31,712
has gone down a lot.

1539
01:06:31,712 --> 01:06:32,813
Why? Why suddenly?

1540
01:06:32,813 --> 01:06:36,617
I think Jeong Yoon's interest in me
isn't that high.

1541
01:06:36,617 --> 01:06:38,752
- He misunderstood.
- That's what I thought.

1542
01:06:38,752 --> 01:06:41,955
When I was choosing,
Do Yoon honestly weighed on my mind most.

1543
01:06:43,357 --> 01:06:44,792
- Hello.
- They missed each other.

1544
01:06:44,792 --> 01:06:46,193
Aren't you cold?
You came out wearing that again.

1545
01:06:46,193 --> 01:06:47,694
Yes, I'm okay.

1546
01:06:47,694 --> 01:06:48,729
- Thank you.
- Have some.

1547
01:06:48,729 --> 01:06:49,930
(After missing each other,
feelings are conveyed again.)

1548
01:06:49,930 --> 01:06:51,498
My heart fluttered a little.

1549
01:06:51,498 --> 01:06:52,266
Really?

1550
01:06:52,266 --> 01:06:53,534
I went there, but he wasn't there.

1551
01:06:53,534 --> 01:06:54,968
He must be with another woman.

1552
01:06:54,968 --> 01:06:56,770
The men will be introduced today.

1553
01:06:56,770 --> 01:06:57,771
Finally.

1554
01:06:57,771 --> 01:06:58,605
My son...

1555
01:06:58,605 --> 01:07:00,407
(The men's jobs and credentials
are revealed.)

1556
01:07:01,375 --> 01:07:02,476
- There it is.
- No wonder.

1557
01:07:02,476 --> 01:07:03,644
There's another licensed profession.

1558
